62#ifndef CATCH_COMPILER_CAPABILITIES_HPP_INCLUDED

65// Detect a number of compiler features - by compiler
66// The following features are defined:
67//
68// CATCH_CONFIG_WINDOWS_SEH : is Windows SEH supported?
69// CATCH_CONFIG_POSIX_SIGNALS : are POSIX signals supported?
70// CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS : Are exceptions enabled?
71// ****************
72// Note to maintainers: if new toggles are added please document them
73// in configuration.md, too
74// ****************
75
76// In general each macro has a _NO_<feature name> form
77// (e.g. CATCH_CONFIG_NO_POSIX_SIGNALS) which disables the feature.
78// Many features, at point of detection, define an _INTERNAL_ macro, so they
79// can be combined, en-mass, with the _NO_ forms later.
80
81

126// Only GCC compiler should be used in this block, so other compilers trying to
127// mask themselves as GCC should be ignored.
128#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && !defined(__ICC) && !defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined(__LCC__) && !defined(__NVCOMPILER)
129# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic push" )

132// This only works on GCC 9+. so we have to also add a global suppression of Wparentheses
133// for older versions of GCC.

135 _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )

153#if defined(__NVCOMPILER)
154# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "diag push" )

156# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS _Pragma( "diag_suppress declared_but_not_referenced" )
157#endif

159#if defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined(__clang__)

161// New pragmas introduced in CUDA 11.5+
162# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "nv_diagnostic push" )
163# define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "nv_diagnostic pop" )
164# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS _Pragma( "nv_diag_suppress 177" )

170// clang-cl defines _MSC_VER as well as __clang__, which could cause the
171// start/stop internal suppression macros to be double defined.
172#if defined(__clang__) && !defined(_MSC_VER)
173
174# define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic push" )
175# define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic pop" )

177#endif // __clang__ && !_MSC_VER

179#if defined(__clang__)
180
181// As of this writing, IBM XL's implementation of __builtin_constant_p has a bug
182// which results in calls to destructors being emitted for each temporary,
183// without a matching initialization. In practice, this can result in something
184// like `std::string::~string` being called on an uninitialized value.
185//
186// For example, this code will likely segfault under IBM XL:
187// ```
188// REQUIRE(std::string("12") + "34" == "1234")
189// ```
190//
191// Similarly, NVHPC's implementation of `__builtin_constant_p` has a bug which
192// results in calls to the immediately evaluated lambda expressions to be
193// reported as unevaluated lambdas.
194// https://developer.nvidia.com/nvidia_bug/3321845.
195//
196// Therefore, `CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN` is not implemented.
197# if !defined(__ibmxl__) && !defined(__CUDACC__) && !defined( __NVCOMPILER )
198# define CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(...) (void)__builtin_constant_p(__VA_ARGS__) /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg, hicpp-vararg) */
199# endif
200
201
202# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
203 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wexit-time-destructors\"" ) \
204 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wglobal-constructors\"")
205
206# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
207 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )
208
209# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
210 _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-variable\"" )
211
212# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \

217
218# define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_COMMA_WARNINGS \

536namespace Catch {
537
538 class IResultCapture;
539 class IConfig;
540
541 class Context {
542 IConfig const* m_config = nullptr;
543 IResultCapture* m_resultCapture = nullptr;
544
545 CATCH_EXPORT static Context* currentContext;
546 friend Context& getCurrentMutableContext();
547 friend Context const& getCurrentContext();
548 static void createContext();
549 friend void cleanUpContext();
550
551 public:
552 IResultCapture* getResultCapture() const { return m_resultCapture; }
553 IConfig const* getConfig() const { return m_config; }
554 void setResultCapture( IResultCapture* resultCapture );
555 void setConfig( IConfig const* config );
556 };
557
558 Context& getCurrentMutableContext();
559
560 inline Context const& getCurrentContext() {
561 // We duplicate the logic from `getCurrentMutableContext` here,
562 // to avoid paying the call overhead in debug mode.
563 if ( !Context::currentContext ) { Context::createContext(); }
564 // NOLINTNEXTLINE(clang-analyzer-core.uninitialized.UndefReturn)
565 return *Context::currentContext;
566 }
567
568 void cleanUpContext();
569
570 class SimplePcg32;
571 SimplePcg32& sharedRng();
572}

670#ifndef CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED
671#define CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED
672
673#include <cstddef>
674#include <string>
675#include <iosfwd>
676#include <cassert>
677
678#include <cstring>
679
680namespace Catch {
681
685 class StringRef {
686 public:
687 using size_type = std::size_t;
688 using const_iterator = const char*;
689
690 private:
691 static constexpr char const* const s_empty = "";
692
693 char const* m_start = s_empty;
694 size_type m_size = 0;
695
696 public: // construction
697 constexpr StringRef() noexcept = default;
698
699 StringRef( char const* rawChars ) noexcept;
700
701 constexpr StringRef( char const* rawChars, size_type size ) noexcept
702 : m_start( rawChars ),
703 m_size( size )
704 {}
705
706 StringRef( std::string const& stdString ) noexcept
707 : m_start( stdString.c_str() ),
708 m_size( stdString.size() )
709 {}
710
711 explicit operator std::string() const {
712 return std::string(m_start, m_size);
713 }
714
715 public: // operators
716 auto operator == ( StringRef other ) const noexcept -> bool {
717 return m_size == other.m_size
718 && (std::memcmp( m_start, other.m_start, m_size ) == 0);
719 }
720 auto operator != (StringRef other) const noexcept -> bool {
721 return !(*this == other);
722 }
723
724 constexpr auto operator[] ( size_type index ) const noexcept -> char {
725 assert(index < m_size);
726 return m_start[index];
727 }
728
729 bool operator<(StringRef rhs) const noexcept;
730
731 public: // named queries
732 constexpr auto empty() const noexcept -> bool {
733 return m_size == 0;
734 }
735 constexpr auto size() const noexcept -> size_type {
736 return m_size;
737 }
738
739 // Returns a substring of [start, start + length).
740 // If start + length > size(), then the substring is [start, start + size()).
741 // If start > size(), then the substring is empty.
742 constexpr StringRef substr(size_type start, size_type length) const noexcept {
743 if (start < m_size) {
744 const auto shortened_size = m_size - start;
745 return StringRef(m_start + start, (shortened_size < length) ? shortened_size : length);
746 } else {
747 return StringRef();
748 }
749 }
750
751 // Returns the current start pointer. May not be null-terminated.
752 constexpr char const* data() const noexcept {
753 return m_start;
754 }
755
756 constexpr const_iterator begin() const { return m_start; }
757 constexpr const_iterator end() const { return m_start + m_size; }
758
759
760 friend std::string& operator += (std::string& lhs, StringRef sr);
761 friend std::ostream& operator << (std::ostream& os, StringRef sr);
762 friend std::string operator+(StringRef lhs, StringRef rhs);
763
770 int compare( StringRef rhs ) const;
771 };
772
773
774 constexpr auto operator ""_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> StringRef {
775 return StringRef( rawChars, size );
776 }
777} // namespace Catch
778
779constexpr auto operator ""_catch_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> Catch::StringRef {
780 return Catch::StringRef( rawChars, size );
781}
782
783#endif // CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED
784

786#ifndef CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
787#define CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
788
789namespace Catch {
790
791 // ResultWas::OfType enum
792 struct ResultWas { enum OfType {
793 Unknown = -1,
794 Ok = 0,
795 Info = 1,
796 Warning = 2,
797 // TODO: Should explicit skip be considered "not OK" (cf. isOk)? I.e., should it have the failure bit?
798 ExplicitSkip = 4,
799
800 FailureBit = 0x10,
801
802 ExpressionFailed = FailureBit | 1,
803 ExplicitFailure = FailureBit | 2,
804
805 Exception = 0x100 | FailureBit,
806
807 ThrewException = Exception | 1,
808 DidntThrowException = Exception | 2,
809
810 FatalErrorCondition = 0x200 | FailureBit
811
812 }; };
813
814 bool isOk( ResultWas::OfType resultType );
815 bool isJustInfo( int flags );
816
817
818 // ResultDisposition::Flags enum
819 struct ResultDisposition { enum Flags {
820 Normal = 0x01,
821
822 ContinueOnFailure = 0x02, // Failures fail test, but execution continues
823 FalseTest = 0x04, // Prefix expression with !
824 SuppressFail = 0x08 // Failures are reported but do not fail the test
825 }; };
826
827 ResultDisposition::Flags operator | ( ResultDisposition::Flags lhs, ResultDisposition::Flags rhs );
828
829 bool shouldContinueOnFailure( int flags );
830 inline bool isFalseTest( int flags ) { return ( flags & ResultDisposition::FalseTest ) != 0; }
831 bool shouldSuppressFailure( int flags );
832
833} // end namespace Catch

835#endif // CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED

838#ifndef CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
839#define CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
840
841#include <cassert>
842#include <type_traits>
843
844
845namespace Catch {
846namespace Detail {
852 template <typename T>
853 class unique_ptr {
854 T* m_ptr;
855 public:
856 constexpr unique_ptr(std::nullptr_t = nullptr):
857 m_ptr{}
858 {}
859 explicit constexpr unique_ptr(T* ptr):
860 m_ptr(ptr)
861 {}
862
863 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
864 unique_ptr(unique_ptr<U>&& from):
865 m_ptr(from.release())
866 {}
867
868 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
869 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr<U>&& from) {
870 reset(from.release());
871
872 return *this;
873 }
874
875 unique_ptr(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
876 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
877
878 unique_ptr(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept:
879 m_ptr(rhs.m_ptr) {
880 rhs.m_ptr = nullptr;
881 }
882 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept {
883 reset(rhs.release());
884
885 return *this;
886 }
887
888 ~unique_ptr() {
889 delete m_ptr;
890 }
891
892 T& operator*() {
893 assert(m_ptr);
894 return *m_ptr;
895 }
896 T const& operator*() const {
897 assert(m_ptr);
898 return *m_ptr;
899 }
900 T* operator->() noexcept {
901 assert(m_ptr);
902 return m_ptr;
903 }
904 T const* operator->() const noexcept {
905 assert(m_ptr);
906 return m_ptr;
907 }
908
909 T* get() { return m_ptr; }
910 T const* get() const { return m_ptr; }
911
912 void reset(T* ptr = nullptr) {
913 delete m_ptr;
914 m_ptr = ptr;
915 }
916
917 T* release() {
918 auto temp = m_ptr;
919 m_ptr = nullptr;
920 return temp;
921 }
922
923 explicit operator bool() const {
924 return m_ptr;
925 }
926
927 friend void swap(unique_ptr& lhs, unique_ptr& rhs) {
928 auto temp = lhs.m_ptr;
929 lhs.m_ptr = rhs.m_ptr;
930 rhs.m_ptr = temp;
931 }
932 };
933
935 template <typename T>
936 class unique_ptr<T[]>;
937
938 template <typename T, typename... Args>
939 unique_ptr<T> make_unique(Args&&... args) {
940 return unique_ptr<T>(new T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
941 }
942
943
944} // end namespace Detail
945} // end namespace Catch
946
947#endif // CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED

1244#ifndef CATCH_ESTIMATE_HPP_INCLUDED

1247namespace Catch {
1248 namespace Benchmark {
1249 template <typename Duration>
1250 struct Estimate {
1251 Duration point;
1252 Duration lower_bound;
1253 Duration upper_bound;
1254 double confidence_interval;
1255
1256 template <typename Duration2>
1257 operator Estimate<Duration2>() const {
1258 return { point, lower_bound, upper_bound, confidence_interval };
1259 }
1260 };
1261 } // namespace Benchmark
1262} // namespace Catch
1263
1264#endif // CATCH_ESTIMATE_HPP_INCLUDED

1267// Adapted from donated nonius code.

1269#ifndef CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1270#define CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1271
1272namespace Catch {
1273 namespace Benchmark {
1274 struct OutlierClassification {
1275 int samples_seen = 0;
1276 int low_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR below Q1
1277 int low_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR below Q1
1278 int high_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR above Q3
1279 int high_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR above Q3
1280
1281 int total() const {
1282 return low_severe + low_mild + high_mild + high_severe;
1283 }
1284 };
1285 } // namespace Benchmark
1286} // namespace Catch
1287
1288#endif // CATCH_OUTLIERS_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1289// The fwd decl & default specialization needs to be seen by VS2017 before
1290// BenchmarkStats itself, or VS2017 will report compilation error.
1291
1292#include <string>
1293#include <vector>
1294
1295namespace Catch {
1296
1297 struct BenchmarkInfo {
1298 std::string name;
1299 double estimatedDuration;
1300 int iterations;
1301 unsigned int samples;
1302 unsigned int resamples;
1303 double clockResolution;
1304 double clockCost;
1305 };
1306
1307 template <class Duration>
1308 struct BenchmarkStats {
1309 BenchmarkInfo info;
1310
1311 std::vector<Duration> samples;
1312 Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> mean;
1313 Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> standardDeviation;
1314 Benchmark::OutlierClassification outliers;
1315 double outlierVariance;
1316
1317 template <typename Duration2>
1318 operator BenchmarkStats<Duration2>() const {
1319 std::vector<Duration2> samples2;
1320 samples2.reserve(samples.size());
1321 for (auto const& sample : samples) {
1322 samples2.push_back(Duration2(sample));
1323 }
1324 return {
1325 info,
1326 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
1327 mean,
1328 standardDeviation,
1329 outliers,
1330 outlierVariance,
1331 };
1332 }
1333 };
1334
1335
1336} // end namespace Catch
1337
1338#endif // CATCH_BENCHMARK_STATS_HPP_INCLUDED

1349namespace Catch {
1350 namespace Benchmark {
1351 template <typename Clock>
1352 using ClockDuration = typename Clock::duration;
1353 template <typename Clock>
1354 using FloatDuration = std::chrono::duration<double, typename Clock::period>;
1355
1356 template <typename Clock>
1357 using TimePoint = typename Clock::time_point;
1358
1359 using default_clock = std::chrono::steady_clock;
1360
1361 template <typename Clock>
1362 struct now {
1363 TimePoint<Clock> operator()() const {
1364 return Clock::now();
1365 }
1366 };
1367
1368 using fp_seconds = std::chrono::duration<double, std::ratio<1>>;
1369 } // namespace Benchmark

1383 template <typename Duration>
1384 struct EnvironmentEstimate {
1385 Duration mean;
1386 OutlierClassification outliers;

1388 template <typename Duration2>
1389 operator EnvironmentEstimate<Duration2>() const {
1390 return { mean, outliers };

1392 };

1428#ifndef CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED

1431#if defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)

1436#include <type_traits>
1437
1438namespace Catch {
1439 namespace Benchmark {
1440#if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
1441 template <typename T>
1442 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1443 asm volatile("" : : "g"(p) : "memory");
1444 }
1445 inline void keep_memory() {
1446 asm volatile("" : : : "memory");
1447 }
1448
1449 namespace Detail {
1450 inline void optimizer_barrier() { keep_memory(); }
1451 } // namespace Detail
1452#elif defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
1453
1454#if defined(_MSVC_VER)
1455#pragma optimize("", off)
1456#elif defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
1457// For IAR the pragma only affects the following function
1458#pragma optimize=disable
1459#endif
1460 template <typename T>
1461 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1462 // thanks @milleniumbug
1463 *reinterpret_cast<char volatile*>(p) = *reinterpret_cast<char const volatile*>(p);
1464 }
1465 // TODO equivalent keep_memory()
1466#if defined(_MSVC_VER)
1467#pragma optimize("", on)
1468#endif
1469
1470 namespace Detail {
1471 inline void optimizer_barrier() {
1472 std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
1473 }
1474 } // namespace Detail
1475
1476#endif
1477
1478 template <typename T>
1479 inline void deoptimize_value(T&& x) {
1480 keep_memory(&x);
1481 }
1482
1483 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1484 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1485 deoptimize_value(CATCH_FORWARD(fn) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
1486 }
1487
1488 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1489 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1490 CATCH_FORWARD(fn) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1491 }
1492 } // namespace Benchmark
1493} // namespace Catch
1494
1495#endif // CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED

1505 struct true_given : std::true_type {};

1507 struct is_callable_tester {
1508 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1509 static true_given<decltype(std::declval<Fun>()(std::declval<Args>()...))> test(int);
1510 template <typename...>
1511 static std::false_type test(...);
1512 };

1514 template <typename T>
1515 struct is_callable;
1516
1517 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1518 struct is_callable<Fun(Args...)> : decltype(is_callable_tester::test<Fun, Args...>(0)) {};

1522 // std::result_of is deprecated in C++17 and removed in C++20. Hence, it is
1523 // replaced with std::invoke_result here.
1524 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1525 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::invoke_result_t<Func, U...>>>;
1526#else
1527 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1528 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::result_of_t<Func(U...)>>>;

1539namespace Catch {
1540 namespace Benchmark {
1541 namespace Detail {
1542 struct ChronometerConcept {
1543 virtual void start() = 0;
1544 virtual void finish() = 0;
1545 virtual ~ChronometerConcept(); // = default;
1546
1547 ChronometerConcept() = default;
1548 ChronometerConcept(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1549 ChronometerConcept& operator=(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1550 };
1551 template <typename Clock>
1552 struct ChronometerModel final : public ChronometerConcept {
1553 void start() override { started = Clock::now(); }
1554 void finish() override { finished = Clock::now(); }
1555
1556 ClockDuration<Clock> elapsed() const { return finished - started; }
1557
1558 TimePoint<Clock> started;
1559 TimePoint<Clock> finished;
1560 };
1561 } // namespace Detail
1562
1563 struct Chronometer {
1564 public:
1565 template <typename Fun>
1566 void measure(Fun&& fun) { measure(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), is_callable<Fun(int)>()); }
1567
1568 int runs() const { return repeats; }
1569
1570 Chronometer(Detail::ChronometerConcept& meter, int repeats_)
1571 : impl(&meter)
1572 , repeats(repeats_) {}
1573
1574 private:
1575 template <typename Fun>
1576 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::false_type) {
1577 measure([&fun](int) { return fun(); }, std::true_type());
1578 }
1579
1580 template <typename Fun>
1581 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::true_type) {
1582 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1583 impl->start();
1584 for (int i = 0; i < repeats; ++i) invoke_deoptimized(fun, i);
1585 impl->finish();
1586 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1587 }
1588
1589 Detail::ChronometerConcept* impl;
1590 int repeats;
1591 };
1592 } // namespace Benchmark
1593} // namespace Catch
1594
1595#endif // CATCH_CHRONOMETER_HPP_INCLUDED

1599namespace Catch {
1600 namespace Benchmark {
1601 namespace Detail {
1602 template <typename T, typename U>
1603 struct is_related
1604 : std::is_same<std::decay_t<T>, std::decay_t<U>> {};
1605
1613 struct BenchmarkFunction {
1614 private:
1615 struct callable {
1616 virtual void call(Chronometer meter) const = 0;
1617 virtual Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> clone() const = 0;
1618 virtual ~callable(); // = default;
1619
1620 callable() = default;
1621 callable(callable const&) = default;
1622 callable& operator=(callable const&) = default;
1623 };
1624 template <typename Fun>
1625 struct model : public callable {
1626 model(Fun&& fun_) : fun(CATCH_MOVE(fun_)) {}
1627 model(Fun const& fun_) : fun(fun_) {}
1628
1629 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> clone() const override {
1630 return Catch::Detail::make_unique<model<Fun>>( *this );
1631 }
1632
1633 void call(Chronometer meter) const override {
1634 call(meter, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
1635 }
1636 void call(Chronometer meter, std::true_type) const {
1637 fun(meter);
1638 }
1639 void call(Chronometer meter, std::false_type) const {
1640 meter.measure(fun);
1641 }
1642
1643 Fun fun;
1644 };
1645
1646 struct do_nothing { void operator()() const {} };
1647
1648 template <typename T>
1649 BenchmarkFunction(model<T>* c) : f(c) {}
1650
1651 public:
1652 BenchmarkFunction()
1653 : f(new model<do_nothing>{ {} }) {}
1654
1655 template <typename Fun,
1656 std::enable_if_t<!is_related<Fun, BenchmarkFunction>::value, int> = 0>
1657 BenchmarkFunction(Fun&& fun)
1658 : f(new model<std::decay_t<Fun>>(CATCH_FORWARD(fun))) {}
1659
1660 BenchmarkFunction( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept:
1661 f( CATCH_MOVE( that.f ) ) {}
1662
1663 BenchmarkFunction(BenchmarkFunction const& that)
1664 : f(that.f->clone()) {}
1665
1666 BenchmarkFunction&
1667 operator=( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept {
1668 f = CATCH_MOVE( that.f );
1669 return *this;
1670 }
1671
1672 BenchmarkFunction& operator=(BenchmarkFunction const& that) {
1673 f = that.f->clone();
1674 return *this;
1675 }
1676
1677 void operator()(Chronometer meter) const { f->call(meter); }
1678
1679 private:
1680 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> f;
1681 };
1682 } // namespace Detail
1683 } // namespace Benchmark
1684} // namespace Catch

1702 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
1703 fun();
1704 }

1739namespace Catch {
1740 namespace Benchmark {
1741 namespace Detail {
1742 template <typename T>
1743 struct CompleteType { using type = T; };
1744 template <>
1745 struct CompleteType<void> { struct type {}; };
1746
1747 template <typename T>
1748 using CompleteType_t = typename CompleteType<T>::type;
1749
1750 template <typename Result>
1751 struct CompleteInvoker {
1752 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1753 static Result invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1754 return CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1755 }
1756 };
1757 template <>
1758 struct CompleteInvoker<void> {
1759 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1760 static CompleteType_t<void> invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1761 CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1762 return {};
1763 }
1764 };
1765
1766 // invoke and not return void :(
1767 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1768 CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>> complete_invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1769 return CompleteInvoker<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>>::invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1770 }
1771
1772 } // namespace Detail
1773
1774 template <typename Fun>
1775 Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun>> user_code(Fun&& fun) {
1776 return Detail::complete_invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun));
1777 }
1778 } // namespace Benchmark
1779} // namespace Catch

1810 template <typename Clock, typename Fun, typename... Args>
1811 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Args...> measure(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1812 auto start = Clock::now();
1813 auto&& r = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1814 auto end = Clock::now();
1815 auto delta = end - start;
1816 return { delta, CATCH_FORWARD(r), 1 };
1817 }
1818 } // namespace Detail
1819 } // namespace Benchmark
1820} // namespace Catch

1826namespace Catch {
1827 namespace Benchmark {
1828 namespace Detail {
1829 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1830 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, int> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::false_type) {
1831 return Detail::measure<Clock>(fun, iters);
1832 }
1833 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1834 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Chronometer> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::true_type) {
1835 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> meter;
1836 auto&& result = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, Chronometer(meter, iters));
1837
1838 return { meter.elapsed(), CATCH_MOVE(result), iters };
1839 }
1840
1841 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1842 using run_for_at_least_argument_t = std::conditional_t<is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>::value, Chronometer, int>;
1843
1844
1845 [[noreturn]]
1846 void throw_optimized_away_error();
1847
1848 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1849 TimingOf<Clock, Fun, run_for_at_least_argument_t<Clock, Fun>>
1850 run_for_at_least(ClockDuration<Clock> how_long,
1851 const int initial_iterations,
1852 Fun&& fun) {
1853 auto iters = initial_iterations;
1854 while (iters < (1 << 30)) {
1855 auto&& Timing = measure_one<Clock>(fun, iters, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
1856
1857 if (Timing.elapsed >= how_long) {
1858 return { Timing.elapsed, CATCH_MOVE(Timing.result), iters };
1859 }
1860 iters *= 2;
1861 }
1862 throw_optimized_away_error();
1863 }
1864 } // namespace Detail
1865 } // namespace Benchmark
1866} // namespace Catch
1867
1868#endif // CATCH_RUN_FOR_AT_LEAST_HPP_INCLUDED

1870#include <vector>
1871
1872namespace Catch {
1873 namespace Benchmark {
1874 template <typename Duration>
1875 struct ExecutionPlan {
1876 int iterations_per_sample;
1877 Duration estimated_duration;
1878 Detail::BenchmarkFunction benchmark;
1879 Duration warmup_time;
1880 int warmup_iterations;
1881
1882 template <typename Duration2>
1883 operator ExecutionPlan<Duration2>() const {
1884 return { iterations_per_sample, estimated_duration, benchmark, warmup_time, warmup_iterations };
1885 }
1886
1887 template <typename Clock>
1888 std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> run(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
1889 // warmup a bit
1890 Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_iterations, Detail::repeat(now<Clock>{}));
1891
1892 std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> times;
1893 const auto num_samples = cfg.benchmarkSamples();
1894 times.reserve( num_samples );
1895 for ( size_t i = 0; i < num_samples; ++i ) {
1896 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> model;
1897 this->benchmark( Chronometer( model, iterations_per_sample ) );
1898 auto sample_time = model.elapsed() - env.clock_cost.mean;
1899 if ( sample_time < FloatDuration<Clock>::zero() ) {
1900 sample_time = FloatDuration<Clock>::zero();
1901 }
1902 times.push_back(sample_time / iterations_per_sample);
1903 }
1904 return times;
1905 }
1906 };
1907 } // namespace Benchmark
1908} // namespace Catch

1933 using sample = std::vector<double>;
1934
1935 // Used when we know we want == comparison of two doubles
1936 // to centralize warning suppression
1937 bool directCompare( double lhs, double rhs );
1938
1939 double weighted_average_quantile(int k, int q, std::vector<double>::iterator first, std::vector<double>::iterator last);
1940
1941 OutlierClassification
1942 classify_outliers( std::vector<double>::const_iterator first,
1943 std::vector<double>::const_iterator last );
1944
1945 double mean( std::vector<double>::const_iterator first,
1946 std::vector<double>::const_iterator last );
1947
1948 template <typename Estimator>
1949 sample jackknife(Estimator&& estimator,
1950 std::vector<double>::iterator first,
1951 std::vector<double>::iterator last) {
1952 auto n = static_cast<size_t>(last - first);
1953 auto second = first;
1954 ++second;
1955 sample results;
1956 results.reserve(n);
1957
1958 for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it) {
1959 std::iter_swap(it, first);
1960 results.push_back(estimator(second, last));
1961 }
1962
1963 return results;
1964 }
1965
1966 inline double normal_cdf(double x) {
1967 return std::erfc(-x / std::sqrt(2.0)) / 2.0;
1968 }
1969
1970 double erfc_inv(double x);
1971
1972 double normal_quantile(double p);
1973
1974 template <typename Estimator>
1975 Estimate<double> bootstrap( double confidence_level,
1976 std::vector<double>::iterator first,
1977 std::vector<double>::iterator last,
1978 sample const& resample,
1979 Estimator&& estimator ) {
1980 auto n_samples = last - first;
1981
1982 double point = estimator(first, last);
1983 // Degenerate case with a single sample
1984 if (n_samples == 1) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
1985
1986 sample jack = jackknife(estimator, first, last);
1987 double jack_mean = mean(jack.begin(), jack.end());
1988 double sum_squares = 0, sum_cubes = 0;
1989 for (double x : jack) {
1990 auto difference = jack_mean - x;
1991 auto square = difference * difference;
1992 auto cube = square * difference;
1993 sum_squares += square; sum_cubes += cube;
1994 }
1995
1996 double accel = sum_cubes / (6 * std::pow(sum_squares, 1.5));
1997 long n = static_cast<long>(resample.size());
1998 double prob_n = std::count_if(resample.begin(), resample.end(), [point](double x) { return x < point; }) / static_cast<double>(n);
1999 // degenerate case with uniform samples
2000 if ( directCompare( prob_n, 0. ) ) {
2001 return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
2002 }
2003
2004 double bias = normal_quantile(prob_n);
2005 double z1 = normal_quantile((1. - confidence_level) / 2.);
2006
2007 auto cumn = [n]( double x ) -> long {
2008 return std::lround( normal_cdf( x ) * static_cast<double>(n) );
2009 };
2010 auto a = [bias, accel](double b) { return bias + b / (1. - accel * b); };
2011 double b1 = bias + z1;
2012 double b2 = bias - z1;
2013 double a1 = a(b1);
2014 double a2 = a(b2);
2015 auto lo = static_cast<size_t>((std::max)(cumn(a1), 0l));
2016 auto hi = static_cast<size_t>((std::min)(cumn(a2), n - 1));
2017
2018 return { point, resample[lo], resample[hi], confidence_level };
2019 }
2020
2021 struct bootstrap_analysis {
2022 Estimate<double> mean;
2023 Estimate<double> standard_deviation;
2024 double outlier_variance;
2025 };
2026
2027 bootstrap_analysis analyse_samples(double confidence_level,
2028 unsigned int n_resamples,
2029 std::vector<double>::iterator first,
2030 std::vector<double>::iterator last);
2031 } // namespace Detail
2032 } // namespace Benchmark
2033} // namespace Catch

2035#endif // CATCH_STATS_HPP_INCLUDED

2037#include <algorithm>
2038#include <vector>
2039#include <cmath>
2040
2041namespace Catch {
2042 namespace Benchmark {
2043 namespace Detail {
2044 template <typename Clock>
2045 std::vector<double> resolution(int k) {
2046 std::vector<TimePoint<Clock>> times;
2047 times.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(k + 1));
2048 for ( int i = 0; i < k + 1; ++i ) {
2049 times.push_back( Clock::now() );
2050 }
2051
2052 std::vector<double> deltas;
2053 deltas.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(k));
2054 for ( size_t idx = 1; idx < times.size(); ++idx ) {
2055 deltas.push_back( static_cast<double>(
2056 ( times[idx] - times[idx - 1] ).count() ) );
2057 }
2058
2059 return deltas;
2060 }
2061
2062 constexpr auto warmup_iterations = 10000;
2063 constexpr auto warmup_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(100);
2064 constexpr auto minimum_ticks = 1000;
2065 constexpr auto warmup_seed = 10000;
2066 constexpr auto clock_resolution_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(500);
2067 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_time_limit = std::chrono::seconds(1);
2068 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit = 100000;
2069 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(10);
2070 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_iterations = 10000;
2071
2072 template <typename Clock>
2073 int warmup() {
2074 return run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_seed, &resolution<Clock>)
2075 .iterations;
2076 }
2077 template <typename Clock>
2078 EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_resolution(int iterations) {
2079 auto r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_resolution_estimation_time), iterations, &resolution<Clock>)
2080 .result;
2081 return {
2082 FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(r.begin(), r.end())),
2083 classify_outliers(r.begin(), r.end()),
2084 };
2085 }
2086 template <typename Clock>
2087 EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_cost(FloatDuration<Clock> resolution) {
2088 auto time_limit = (std::min)(
2089 resolution * clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit,
2090 FloatDuration<Clock>(clock_cost_estimation_time_limit));
2091 auto time_clock = [](int k) {
2092 return Detail::measure<Clock>([k] {
2093 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2094 volatile auto ignored = Clock::now();
2095 (void)ignored;
2096 }
2097 }).elapsed;
2098 };
2099 time_clock(1);
2100 int iters = clock_cost_estimation_iterations;
2101 auto&& r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_cost_estimation_time), iters, time_clock);
2102 std::vector<double> times;
2103 int nsamples = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(time_limit / r.elapsed));
2104 times.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(nsamples));
2105 for ( int s = 0; s < nsamples; ++s ) {
2106 times.push_back( static_cast<double>(
2107 ( time_clock( r.iterations ) / r.iterations )
2108 .count() ) );
2109 }
2110 return {
2111 FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(times.begin(), times.end())),
2112 classify_outliers(times.begin(), times.end()),
2113 };
2114 }
2115
2116 template <typename Clock>
2117 Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> measure_environment() {
2118#if defined(__clang__)
2119# pragma clang diagnostic push
2120# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wexit-time-destructors"
2121#endif
2122 static Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>> env;
2123#if defined(__clang__)
2124# pragma clang diagnostic pop
2125#endif
2126 if (env) {
2127 return *env;
2128 }
2129
2130 auto iters = Detail::warmup<Clock>();
2131 auto resolution = Detail::estimate_clock_resolution<Clock>(iters);
2132 auto cost = Detail::estimate_clock_cost<Clock>(resolution.mean);
2133
2134 env = Catch::Detail::make_unique<Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>>( Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>{resolution, cost} );
2135 return *env;
2136 }
2137 } // namespace Detail
2138 } // namespace Benchmark

2159namespace Catch {
2160 namespace Benchmark {
2161 template <typename Duration>
2162 struct SampleAnalysis {
2163 std::vector<Duration> samples;
2164 Estimate<Duration> mean;
2165 Estimate<Duration> standard_deviation;
2166 OutlierClassification outliers;
2167 double outlier_variance;
2168
2169 template <typename Duration2>
2170 operator SampleAnalysis<Duration2>() const {
2171 std::vector<Duration2> samples2;
2172 samples2.reserve(samples.size());
2173 for (auto const& d : samples) {
2174 samples2.push_back(Duration2(d));
2175 }
2176 return {
2177 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
2178 mean,
2179 standard_deviation,
2180 outliers,
2181 outlier_variance,
2182 };
2183 }
2184 };
2185 } // namespace Benchmark
2186} // namespace Catch
2187
2188#endif // CATCH_SAMPLE_ANALYSIS_HPP_INCLUDED
2189
2190#include <vector>
2191
2192namespace Catch {
2193 namespace Benchmark {
2194 namespace Detail {
2195 template <typename Duration, typename Iterator>
2196 SampleAnalysis<Duration> analyse(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<Duration>, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2197 if (!cfg.benchmarkNoAnalysis()) {
2198 std::vector<double> samples;
2199 samples.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
2200 for (auto current = first; current != last; ++current) {
2201 samples.push_back( current->count() );
2202 }
2203
2204 auto analysis = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::analyse_samples(cfg.benchmarkConfidenceInterval(), cfg.benchmarkResamples(), samples.begin(), samples.end());
2205 auto outliers = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::classify_outliers(samples.begin(), samples.end());
2206
2207 auto wrap_estimate = [](Estimate<double> e) {
2208 return Estimate<Duration> {
2209 Duration(e.point),
2210 Duration(e.lower_bound),
2211 Duration(e.upper_bound),
2212 e.confidence_interval,
2213 };
2214 };
2215 std::vector<Duration> samples2;
2216 samples2.reserve(samples.size());
2217 for (auto s : samples) {
2218 samples2.push_back( Duration( s ) );
2219 }
2220
2221 return {
2222 CATCH_MOVE(samples2),
2223 wrap_estimate(analysis.mean),
2224 wrap_estimate(analysis.standard_deviation),
2225 outliers,
2226 analysis.outlier_variance,
2227 };
2228 } else {
2229 std::vector<Duration> samples;
2230 samples.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
2231
2232 Duration mean = Duration(0);
2233 int i = 0;
2234 for (auto it = first; it < last; ++it, ++i) {
2235 samples.push_back(Duration(*it));
2236 mean += Duration(*it);
2237 }
2238 mean /= i;
2239
2240 return {
2241 CATCH_MOVE(samples),
2242 Estimate<Duration>{mean, mean, mean, 0.0},
2243 Estimate<Duration>{Duration(0), Duration(0), Duration(0), 0.0},
2244 OutlierClassification{},
2245 0.0
2246 };
2247 }
2248 }
2249 } // namespace Detail
2250 } // namespace Benchmark
2251} // namespace Catch
2252
2253#endif // CATCH_ANALYSE_HPP_INCLUDED
2254
2255#include <algorithm>
2256#include <chrono>
2257#include <exception>
2258#include <functional>
2259#include <string>
2260#include <vector>
2261#include <cmath>
2262
2263namespace Catch {
2264 namespace Benchmark {
2265 struct Benchmark {
2266 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName)
2267 : name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2268
2269 template <class FUN>
2270 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName , FUN &&func)
2271 : fun(CATCH_MOVE(func)), name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2272
2273 template <typename Clock>
2274 ExecutionPlan<FloatDuration<Clock>> prepare(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
2275 auto min_time = env.clock_resolution.mean * Detail::minimum_ticks;
2276 auto run_time = std::max(min_time, std::chrono::duration_cast<decltype(min_time)>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()));
2277 auto&& test = Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(run_time), 1, fun);
2278 int new_iters = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(min_time * test.iterations / test.elapsed));
2279 return { new_iters, test.elapsed / test.iterations * new_iters * cfg.benchmarkSamples(), fun, std::chrono::duration_cast<FloatDuration<Clock>>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()), Detail::warmup_iterations };
2280 }
2281
2282 template <typename Clock = default_clock>
2283 void run() {
2284 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2285
2286 auto env = Detail::measure_environment<Clock>();
2287
2288 getResultCapture().benchmarkPreparing(name);
2289 CATCH_TRY{
2290 auto plan = user_code([&] {
2291 return prepare<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2292 });
2293
2294 BenchmarkInfo info {
2295 CATCH_MOVE(name),
2296 plan.estimated_duration.count(),
2297 plan.iterations_per_sample,
2298 cfg->benchmarkSamples(),
2299 cfg->benchmarkResamples(),
2300 env.clock_resolution.mean.count(),
2301 env.clock_cost.mean.count()
2302 };
2303
2304 getResultCapture().benchmarkStarting(info);
2305
2306 auto samples = user_code([&] {
2307 return plan.template run<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2308 });
2309
2310 auto analysis = Detail::analyse(*cfg, env, samples.begin(), samples.end());
2311 BenchmarkStats<FloatDuration<Clock>> stats{ CATCH_MOVE(info), CATCH_MOVE(analysis.samples), analysis.mean, analysis.standard_deviation, analysis.outliers, analysis.outlier_variance };
2312 getResultCapture().benchmarkEnded(stats);
2313 } CATCH_CATCH_ANON (TestFailureException const&) {
2314 getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed("Benchmark failed due to failed assertion"_sr);
2315 } CATCH_CATCH_ALL{
2316 getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed(translateActiveException());
2317 // We let the exception go further up so that the
2318 // test case is marked as failed.
2319 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
2320 }
2321 }
2322
2323 // sets lambda to be used in fun *and* executes benchmark!
2324 template <typename Fun, std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_related<Fun, Benchmark>::value, int> = 0>
2325 Benchmark & operator=(Fun func) {
2326 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2327 if (!cfg->skipBenchmarks()) {
2328 fun = Detail::BenchmarkFunction(func);
2329 run();
2330 }
2331 return *this;
2332 }
2333
2334 explicit operator bool() {
2335 return true;
2336 }
2337
2338 private:
2339 Detail::BenchmarkFunction fun;
2340 std::string name;
2341 };
2342 }
2343} // namespace Catch
2344
2345#define INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_1_ARG(arg1, arg2, ...) arg1
2346#define INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_2_ARG(arg1, arg2, ...) arg2

2349 if( Catch::Benchmark::Benchmark BenchmarkName{name} ) \

2351
2352#define INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(BenchmarkName, name)\
2353 if( Catch::Benchmark::Benchmark BenchmarkName{name} ) \
2354 BenchmarkName = [&]
2355
2356#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL)
2357
2358#define CATCH_BENCHMARK(...) \
2359 INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(CATCH2_INTERNAL_BENCHMARK_), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_1_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_2_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,))
2360#define CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(name) \
2361 INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(CATCH2_INTERNAL_BENCHMARK_), name)
2362
2363#else

2367#define BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(name) \

2378#define CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2380
2381#include <type_traits>
2382
2383namespace Catch {
2384 namespace Benchmark {
2385 namespace Detail {
2386 template <typename T, bool Destruct>
2387 struct ObjectStorage
2388 {
2389 ObjectStorage() = default;
2390
2391 ObjectStorage(const ObjectStorage& other)
2392 {
2393 new(&data) T(other.stored_object());
2394 }
2395
2396 ObjectStorage(ObjectStorage&& other)
2397 {
2398 new(data) T(CATCH_MOVE(other.stored_object()));
2399 }
2400
2401 ~ObjectStorage() { destruct_on_exit<T>(); }
2402
2403 template <typename... Args>
2404 void construct(Args&&... args)
2405 {
2406 new (data) T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
2407 }
2408
2409 template <bool AllowManualDestruction = !Destruct>
2410 std::enable_if_t<AllowManualDestruction> destruct()
2411 {
2412 stored_object().~T();
2413 }
2414
2415 private:
2416 // If this is a constructor benchmark, destruct the underlying object
2417 template <typename U>
2418 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { destruct<true>(); }
2419 // Otherwise, don't
2420 template <typename U>
2421 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<!Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { }
2422
2423#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2424# pragma GCC diagnostic push
2425# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wstrict-aliasing"
2426#endif
2427 T& stored_object() { return *reinterpret_cast<T*>( data ); }
2428
2429 T const& stored_object() const {
2430 return *reinterpret_cast<T const*>( data );
2431 }
2432#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2433# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2434#endif
2435
2436 alignas( T ) unsigned char data[sizeof( T )]{};
2437 };
2438 } // namespace Detail
2439
2440 template <typename T>
2441 using storage_for = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, true>;
2442
2443 template <typename T>
2444 using destructable_object = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, false>;
2445 } // namespace Benchmark
2446} // namespace Catch
2447
2448#endif // CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2507namespace Catch {
2508
2509 class ReusableStringStream : Detail::NonCopyable {
2510 std::size_t m_index;
2511 std::ostream* m_oss;
2512 public:
2513 ReusableStringStream();
2514 ~ReusableStringStream();
2515
2517 std::string str() const;
2519 void str(std::string const& str);
2520
2521#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2522#pragma GCC diagnostic push
2523// Old versions of GCC do not understand -Wnonnull-compare
2524#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wpragmas"
2525// Streaming a function pointer triggers Waddress and Wnonnull-compare
2526// on GCC, because it implicitly converts it to bool and then decides
2527// that the check it uses (a? true : false) is tautological and cannot
2528// be null...
2529#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Waddress"
2530#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wnonnull-compare"
2531#endif
2532
2533 template<typename T>
2534 auto operator << ( T const& value ) -> ReusableStringStream& {
2535 *m_oss << value;
2536 return *this;
2537 }
2538
2539#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2540#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2541#endif
2542 auto get() -> std::ostream& { return *m_oss; }
2543 };
2544}

2629 inline std::size_t catch_strnlen(const char *str, std::size_t n) {
2630 auto ret = std::char_traits<char>::find(str, n, '\0');
2631 if (ret != nullptr) {
2632 return static_cast<std::size_t>(ret - str);
2633 }
2634 return n;
2635 }

2653 template<typename T>
2654 class IsStreamInsertable {
2655 template<typename Stream, typename U>
2656 static auto test(int)
2657 -> decltype(std::declval<Stream&>() << std::declval<U>(), std::true_type());
2658
2659 template<typename, typename>
2660 static auto test(...)->std::false_type;
2661
2662 public:
2663 static const bool value = decltype(test<std::ostream, const T&>(0))::value;
2664 };

2667 std::string convertUnknownEnumToString( E e );
2668

2670 std::enable_if_t<
2671 !std::is_enum<T>::value && !std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
2672 std::string> convertUnstreamable( T const& ) {
2673 return std::string(Detail::unprintableString);
2674 }
2675 template<typename T>
2676 std::enable_if_t<
2677 !std::is_enum<T>::value && std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
2678 std::string> convertUnstreamable(T const& ex) {
2679 return ex.what();
2680 }

2688 }

2705 template <typename T, typename = void>
2706 struct StringMaker {
2707 template <typename Fake = T>
2708 static
2709 std::enable_if_t<::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
2710 convert(const Fake& value) {
2711 ReusableStringStream rss;
2712 // NB: call using the function-like syntax to avoid ambiguity with
2713 // user-defined templated operator<< under clang.
2714 rss.operator<<(value);
2715 return rss.str();
2716 }
2717
2718 template <typename Fake = T>
2719 static
2720 std::enable_if_t<!::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
2721 convert( const Fake& value ) {
2722#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER)
2723 return Detail::convertUnstreamable(value);
2724#else
2725 return CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER(value);
2726#endif
2727 }

2858 return b ? "true"s : "false"s;
2859 }
2860 };

2926
2927 namespace Detail {
2928 template<typename InputIterator, typename Sentinel = InputIterator>
2929 std::string rangeToString(InputIterator first, Sentinel last) {
2930 ReusableStringStream rss;
2931 rss << "{ ";
2932 if (first != last) {
2933 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
2934 for (++first; first != last; ++first)
2935 rss << ", " << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
2936 }
2937 rss << " }";
2938 return rss.str();
2939 }
2940 }
2941
2942} // namespace Catch

2999 >
3000 struct TupleElementPrinter {

3002 os << (N ? ", " : " ")
3003 << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(std::get<N>(tuple));

3083 template<typename Range>
3084 std::string rangeToString( Range const& range ) {
3085 return ::Catch::Detail::rangeToString( begin( range ), end( range ) );
3086 }
3087
3088 // Handle vector<bool> specially
3089 template<typename Allocator>
3090 std::string rangeToString( std::vector<bool, Allocator> const& v ) {
3091 ReusableStringStream rss;
3092 rss << "{ ";
3093 bool first = true;
3094 for( bool b : v ) {
3095 if( first )
3096 first = false;
3097 else
3098 rss << ", ";
3099 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify( b );
3100 }
3101 rss << " }";
3102 return rss.str();
3103 }

3106 struct StringMaker<R, std::enable_if_t<is_range<R>::value && !::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<R>::value>> {
3107 static std::string convert( R const& range ) {
3108 return rangeToString( range );
3109 }
3110 };

3130template <class Ratio>
3131struct ratio_string {
3132 static std::string symbol() {
3133 Catch::ReusableStringStream rss;
3134 rss << '[' << Ratio::num << '/'
3135 << Ratio::den << ']';
3136 return rss.str();
3137 }
3138};

3141struct ratio_string<std::atto> {
3142 static char symbol() { return 'a'; }
3143};
3144template <>
3145struct ratio_string<std::femto> {
3146 static char symbol() { return 'f'; }
3147};
3148template <>
3149struct ratio_string<std::pico> {
3150 static char symbol() { return 'p'; }
3151};
3152template <>
3153struct ratio_string<std::nano> {
3154 static char symbol() { return 'n'; }
3155};
3156template <>
3157struct ratio_string<std::micro> {
3158 static char symbol() { return 'u'; }
3159};
3160template <>
3161struct ratio_string<std::milli> {
3162 static char symbol() { return 'm'; }
3163};

3170 ReusableStringStream rss;
3171 rss << duration.count() << ' ' << ratio_string<Ratio>::symbol() << 's';
3172 return rss.str();
3173 }

3201 // std::chrono::time_point specialization
3202 // Generic time_point cannot be specialized, only std::chrono::time_point<system_clock>
3203 template<typename Clock, typename Duration>
3204 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration>> {
3205 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3206 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(time_point.time_since_epoch()) + " since epoch";
3207 }
3208 };
3209 // std::chrono::time_point<system_clock> specialization
3210 template<typename Duration>
3211 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration>> {
3212 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3213 auto converted = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(time_point);
3214
3215#ifdef _MSC_VER
3216 std::tm timeInfo = {};
3217 gmtime_s(&timeInfo, &converted);
3218#else
3219 std::tm* timeInfo = std::gmtime(&converted);
3220#endif
3221
3222 auto const timeStampSize = sizeof("2017-01-16T17:06:45Z");
3223 char timeStamp[timeStampSize];
3224 const char * const fmt = "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ";
3225
3226#ifdef _MSC_VER
3227 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, &timeInfo);
3228#else
3229 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, timeInfo);
3230#endif
3231 return std::string(timeStamp, timeStampSize - 1);
3232 }
3233 };
3234}

3241 static const auto& enumInfo = ::Catch::getMutableRegistryHub().getMutableEnumValuesRegistry().registerEnum( #enumName, #__VA_ARGS__, { __VA_ARGS__ } ); \
3242 return static_cast<std::string>(enumInfo.lookup( static_cast<int>( value ) )); \
3243 } \
3244 }; \
3245}

3255#include <type_traits>

3257namespace Catch {
3258
3259 class Approx {
3260 private:
3261 bool equalityComparisonImpl(double other) const;
3262 // Sets and validates the new margin (margin >= 0)
3263 void setMargin(double margin);
3264 // Sets and validates the new epsilon (0 < epsilon < 1)
3265 void setEpsilon(double epsilon);
3266
3267 public:
3268 explicit Approx ( double value );
3269
3270 static Approx custom();
3271
3272 Approx operator-() const;
3273
3274 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3275 Approx operator()( T const& value ) const {
3276 Approx approx( static_cast<double>(value) );
3277 approx.m_epsilon = m_epsilon;
3278 approx.m_margin = m_margin;
3279 approx.m_scale = m_scale;
3280 return approx;
3281 }
3282
3283 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3284 explicit Approx( T const& value ): Approx(static_cast<double>(value))
3285 {}
3286
3287
3288 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3289 friend bool operator == ( const T& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3290 auto lhs_v = static_cast<double>(lhs);
3291 return rhs.equalityComparisonImpl(lhs_v);
3292 }
3293
3294 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3295 friend bool operator == ( Approx const& lhs, const T& rhs ) {
3296 return operator==( rhs, lhs );
3297 }
3298
3299 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3300 friend bool operator != ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3301 return !operator==( lhs, rhs );
3302 }
3303
3304 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3305 friend bool operator != ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3306 return !operator==( rhs, lhs );
3307 }
3308
3309 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3310 friend bool operator <= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3311 return static_cast<double>(lhs) < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3312 }
3313
3314 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3315 friend bool operator <= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3316 return lhs.m_value < static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3317 }
3318
3319 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3320 friend bool operator >= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3321 return static_cast<double>(lhs) > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3322 }
3323
3324 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3325 friend bool operator >= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3326 return lhs.m_value > static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3327 }
3328
3329 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3330 Approx& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
3331 const auto epsilonAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newEpsilon);
3332 setEpsilon(epsilonAsDouble);
3333 return *this;
3334 }
3335
3336 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3337 Approx& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
3338 const auto marginAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newMargin);
3339 setMargin(marginAsDouble);
3340 return *this;
3341 }
3342
3343 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3344 Approx& scale( T const& newScale ) {
3345 m_scale = static_cast<double>(newScale);
3346 return *this;
3347 }
3348
3349 std::string toString() const;
3350
3351 private:
3352 double m_epsilon;
3353 double m_margin;
3354 double m_scale;
3355 double m_value;
3356 };

3361} // end namespace literals

3592 return out;
3593 }
3594
3595 std::string const m_name;
3596 };
3597

3606 };

3672#define CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED
3673
3674
3675#include <cassert>
3676
3677namespace Catch {
3678
3679 // An optional type
3680 template<typename T>
3681 class Optional {
3682 public:
3683 Optional(): nullableValue( nullptr ) {}
3684 ~Optional() { reset(); }
3685
3686 Optional( T const& _value ):
3687 nullableValue( new ( storage ) T( _value ) ) {}
3688 Optional( T&& _value ):
3689 nullableValue( new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( _value ) ) ) {}
3690
3691 Optional& operator=( T const& _value ) {
3692 reset();
3693 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( _value );
3694 return *this;
3695 }
3696 Optional& operator=( T&& _value ) {
3697 reset();
3698 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( _value ) );
3699 return *this;
3700 }
3701
3702 Optional( Optional const& _other ):
3703 nullableValue( _other ? new ( storage ) T( *_other ) : nullptr ) {}
3704 Optional( Optional&& _other ):
3705 nullableValue( _other ? new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( *_other ) )
3706 : nullptr ) {}
3707
3708 Optional& operator=( Optional const& _other ) {
3709 if ( &_other != this ) {
3710 reset();
3711 if ( _other ) { nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( *_other ); }
3712 }
3713 return *this;
3714 }
3715 Optional& operator=( Optional&& _other ) {
3716 if ( &_other != this ) {
3717 reset();
3718 if ( _other ) {
3719 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( *_other ) );
3720 }
3721 }
3722 return *this;
3723 }
3724
3725 void reset() {
3726 if ( nullableValue ) { nullableValue->~T(); }
3727 nullableValue = nullptr;
3728 }
3729
3730 T& operator*() {
3731 assert(nullableValue);
3732 return *nullableValue;
3733 }
3734 T const& operator*() const {
3735 assert(nullableValue);
3736 return *nullableValue;
3737 }
3738 T* operator->() {
3739 assert(nullableValue);
3740 return nullableValue;
3741 }
3742 const T* operator->() const {
3743 assert(nullableValue);
3744 return nullableValue;
3745 }
3746
3747 T valueOr( T const& defaultValue ) const {
3748 return nullableValue ? *nullableValue : defaultValue;
3749 }
3750
3751 bool some() const { return nullableValue != nullptr; }
3752 bool none() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
3753
3754 bool operator !() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
3755 explicit operator bool() const {
3756 return some();
3757 }
3758
3759 friend bool operator==(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
3760 if (a.none() && b.none()) {
3761 return true;
3762 } else if (a.some() && b.some()) {
3763 return *a == *b;
3764 } else {
3765 return false;
3766 }
3767 }
3768 friend bool operator!=(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
3769 return !( a == b );
3770 }
3771
3772 private:
3773 T* nullableValue;
3774 alignas(alignof(T)) char storage[sizeof(T)];
3775 };
3776
3777} // end namespace Catch
3778
3779#endif // CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED
3780

4232 class IResultCapture;
4233
4234 struct MessageStream {
4235
4236 template<typename T>
4237 MessageStream& operator << ( T const& value ) {
4238 m_stream << value;
4239 return *this;
4240 }
4241
4242 ReusableStringStream m_stream;
4243 };
4244
4245 struct MessageBuilder : MessageStream {
4246 MessageBuilder( StringRef macroName,
4247 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo,
4248 ResultWas::OfType type ):
4249 m_info(macroName, lineInfo, type) {}
4250
4251 template<typename T>
4252 MessageBuilder&& operator << ( T const& value ) && {
4253 m_stream << value;
4254 return CATCH_MOVE(*this);
4255 }
4256
4257 MessageInfo m_info;
4258 };
4259
4260 class ScopedMessage {
4261 public:
4262 explicit ScopedMessage( MessageBuilder&& builder );
4263 ScopedMessage( ScopedMessage& duplicate ) = delete;
4264 ScopedMessage( ScopedMessage&& old ) noexcept;
4265 ~ScopedMessage();
4266
4267 MessageInfo m_info;
4268 bool m_moved = false;
4269 };
4270
4271 class Capturer {
4272 std::vector<MessageInfo> m_messages;
4273 IResultCapture& m_resultCapture;
4274 size_t m_captured = 0;
4275 public:
4276 Capturer( StringRef macroName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, ResultWas::OfType resultType, StringRef names );
4277
4278 Capturer(Capturer const&) = delete;
4279 Capturer& operator=(Capturer const&) = delete;
4280
4281 ~Capturer();
4282
4283 void captureValue( size_t index, std::string const& value );
4284
4285 template<typename T>
4286 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value ) {
4287 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify( value ) );
4288 }
4289
4290 template<typename T, typename... Ts>
4291 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value, Ts const&... values ) {
4292 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify(value) );
4293 captureValues( index+1, values... );
4294 }
4295 };

4297} // end namespace Catch

4300#define INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( macroName, messageType, resultDisposition, ... ) \
4301 do { \
4302 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), resultDisposition ); \
4303 catchAssertionHandler.handleMessage( messageType, ( Catch::MessageStream() << __VA_ARGS__ + ::Catch::StreamEndStop() ).m_stream.str() ); \
4304 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
4305 } while( false )
4306
4308#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( varName, macroName, ... ) \
4309 Catch::Capturer varName( macroName##_catch_sr, \
4310 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
4311 Catch::ResultWas::Info, \
4312 #__VA_ARGS__##_catch_sr ); \
4313 varName.captureValues( 0, __VA_ARGS__ )
4314
4316#define INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4317 const Catch::ScopedMessage INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( scopedMessage )( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4318
4320#define INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4321 Catch::getResultCapture().emplaceUnscopedMessage( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4322
4323
4324#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4325
4326 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "CATCH_INFO", msg )
4327 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4328 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4329 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CATCH_CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )
4330
4331#elif defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4332
4333 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4334 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4335 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) (void)(0)
4336 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) (void)(0)
4337
4338#elif !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4339
4340 #define INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "INFO", msg )
4341 #define UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4342 #define WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4343 #define CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )

4404 struct SectionInfo {
4405 // The last argument is ignored, so that people can write
4406 // SECTION("ShortName", "Proper description that is long") and
4407 // still use the `-c` flag comfortably.
4408 SectionInfo( SourceLineInfo const& _lineInfo, std::string _name,
4409 const char* const = nullptr ):
4410 name(CATCH_MOVE(_name)),
4411 lineInfo(_lineInfo)
4412 {}
4413
4414 std::string name;
4415 SourceLineInfo lineInfo;
4416 };
4417
4418 struct SectionEndInfo {
4419 SectionInfo sectionInfo;
4420 Counts prevAssertions;
4421 double durationInSeconds;
4422 };
4423
4424} // end namespace Catch

4478 // enum of result types from a parse
4479 enum class ParseResultType {
4480 Matched,
4481 NoMatch,
4482 ShortCircuitAll,
4483 ShortCircuitSame

4486 struct accept_many_t {};
4487 constexpr accept_many_t accept_many {};

4489 namespace Detail {
4490 struct fake_arg {
4491 template <typename T>
4492 operator T();
4493 };
4494
4495 template <typename F, typename = void>
4496 struct is_unary_function : std::false_type {};
4497
4498 template <typename F>
4499 struct is_unary_function<
4500 F,
4501 Catch::Detail::void_t<decltype(
4502 std::declval<F>()( fake_arg() ) )
4503 >
4504 > : std::true_type {};
4505
4506 // Traits for extracting arg and return type of lambdas (for single
4507 // argument lambdas)
4508 template <typename L>
4509 struct UnaryLambdaTraits
4510 : UnaryLambdaTraits<decltype( &L::operator() )> {};
4511
4512 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename... Args>
4513 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( Args... ) const> {
4514 static const bool isValid = false;
4515 };
4516
4517 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename ArgT>
4518 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( ArgT ) const> {
4519 static const bool isValid = true;
4520 using ArgType = std::remove_const_t<std::remove_reference_t<ArgT>>;
4521 using ReturnType = ReturnT;
4522 };
4523
4524 class TokenStream;
4525
4526 // Wraps a token coming from a token stream. These may not directly
4527 // correspond to strings as a single string may encode an option +
4528 // its argument if the : or = form is used
4529 enum class TokenType { Option, Argument };
4530 struct Token {
4531 TokenType type;
4532 std::string token;
4533 };
4534
4535 // Abstracts iterators into args as a stream of tokens, with option
4536 // arguments uniformly handled
4537 class TokenStream {
4538 using Iterator = std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator;
4539 Iterator it;
4540 Iterator itEnd;
4541 std::vector<Token> m_tokenBuffer;
4542
4543 void loadBuffer();
4544
4545 public:
4546 explicit TokenStream( Args const& args );
4547 TokenStream( Iterator it, Iterator itEnd );
4548
4549 explicit operator bool() const {
4550 return !m_tokenBuffer.empty() || it != itEnd;
4551 }
4552
4553 size_t count() const {
4554 return m_tokenBuffer.size() + ( itEnd - it );
4555 }
4556
4557 Token operator*() const {
4558 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4559 return m_tokenBuffer.front();
4560 }
4561
4562 Token const* operator->() const {
4563 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4564 return &m_tokenBuffer.front();
4565 }
4566
4567 TokenStream& operator++();
4568 };
4569
4571 enum class ResultType {
4572 Ok,
4573 LogicError,
4575 RuntimeError
4576 };
4577
4578 class ResultBase {
4579 protected:
4580 ResultBase( ResultType type ): m_type( type ) {}
4581 virtual ~ResultBase(); // = default;
4582
4583
4584 ResultBase(ResultBase const&) = default;
4585 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase const&) = default;
4586 ResultBase(ResultBase&&) = default;
4587 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase&&) = default;
4588
4589 virtual void enforceOk() const = 0;
4590
4591 ResultType m_type;
4592 };
4593
4594 template <typename T> class ResultValueBase : public ResultBase {
4595 public:
4596 auto value() const -> T const& {
4597 enforceOk();
4598 return m_value;
4599 }
4600
4601 protected:
4602 ResultValueBase( ResultType type ): ResultBase( type ) {}
4603
4604 ResultValueBase( ResultValueBase const& other ):
4605 ResultBase( other ) {
4606 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4607 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4608 }
4609
4610 ResultValueBase( ResultType, T const& value ): ResultBase( ResultType::Ok ) {
4611 new ( &m_value ) T( value );
4612 }
4613
4614 auto operator=( ResultValueBase const& other )
4615 -> ResultValueBase& {
4616 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4617 m_value.~T();
4618 ResultBase::operator=( other );
4619 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4620 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4621 return *this;
4622 }
4623
4624 ~ResultValueBase() override {
4625 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4626 m_value.~T();
4627 }
4628
4629 union {
4630 T m_value;
4631 };
4632 };
4633
4634 template <> class ResultValueBase<void> : public ResultBase {
4635 protected:
4636 using ResultBase::ResultBase;
4637 };
4638
4639 template <typename T = void>
4640 class BasicResult : public ResultValueBase<T> {
4641 public:
4642 template <typename U>
4643 explicit BasicResult( BasicResult<U> const& other ):
4644 ResultValueBase<T>( other.type() ),
4645 m_errorMessage( other.errorMessage() ) {
4646 assert( type() != ResultType::Ok );
4647 }
4648
4649 template <typename U>
4650 static auto ok( U const& value ) -> BasicResult {
4651 return { ResultType::Ok, value };
4652 }
4653 static auto ok() -> BasicResult { return { ResultType::Ok }; }
4654 static auto logicError( std::string&& message )
4655 -> BasicResult {
4656 return { ResultType::LogicError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4657 }
4658 static auto runtimeError( std::string&& message )
4659 -> BasicResult {
4660 return { ResultType::RuntimeError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4661 }
4662
4663 explicit operator bool() const {
4664 return m_type == ResultType::Ok;
4665 }
4666 auto type() const -> ResultType { return m_type; }
4667 auto errorMessage() const -> std::string const& {
4668 return m_errorMessage;
4669 }
4670
4671 protected:
4672 void enforceOk() const override {
4673
4674 // Errors shouldn't reach this point, but if they do
4675 // the actual error message will be in m_errorMessage
4676 assert( m_type != ResultType::LogicError );
4677 assert( m_type != ResultType::RuntimeError );
4678 if ( m_type != ResultType::Ok )
4679 std::abort();
4680 }
4681
4682 std::string
4683 m_errorMessage; // Only populated if resultType is an error
4684
4685 BasicResult( ResultType type,
4686 std::string&& message ):
4687 ResultValueBase<T>( type ), m_errorMessage( CATCH_MOVE(message) ) {
4688 assert( m_type != ResultType::Ok );
4689 }
4690
4691 using ResultValueBase<T>::ResultValueBase;
4692 using ResultBase::m_type;
4693 };
4694
4695 class ParseState {
4696 public:
4697 ParseState( ParseResultType type,
4698 TokenStream const& remainingTokens );
4699
4700 ParseResultType type() const { return m_type; }
4701 TokenStream const& remainingTokens() const {
4702 return m_remainingTokens;
4703 }
4704
4705 private:
4706 ParseResultType m_type;
4707 TokenStream m_remainingTokens;
4708 };
4709
4710 using Result = BasicResult<void>;
4711 using ParserResult = BasicResult<ParseResultType>;
4712 using InternalParseResult = BasicResult<ParseState>;
4713
4714 struct HelpColumns {
4715 std::string left;
4716 std::string right;
4717 };
4718
4719 template <typename T>
4720 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, T& target ) {
4721 std::stringstream ss( source );
4722 ss >> target;
4723 if ( ss.fail() ) {
4724 return ParserResult::runtimeError(
4725 "Unable to convert '" + source +
4726 "' to destination type" );
4727 } else {
4728 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4729 }
4730 }
4731 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source,
4732 std::string& target );
4733 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, bool& target );
4734
4735#ifdef CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4736 template <typename T>
4737 auto convertInto( std::string const& source,
4738 CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE<T>& target )
4739 -> ParserResult {
4740 T temp;
4741 auto result = convertInto( source, temp );
4742 if ( result )
4743 target = CATCH_MOVE( temp );
4744 return result;
4745 }
4746#endif // CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4747
4748 struct BoundRef : Catch::Detail::NonCopyable {
4749 virtual ~BoundRef() = default;
4750 virtual bool isContainer() const;
4751 virtual bool isFlag() const;
4752 };
4753 struct BoundValueRefBase : BoundRef {
4754 virtual auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4755 -> ParserResult = 0;
4756 };
4757 struct BoundFlagRefBase : BoundRef {
4758 virtual auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult = 0;
4759 bool isFlag() const override;
4760 };
4761
4762 template <typename T> struct BoundValueRef : BoundValueRefBase {
4763 T& m_ref;
4764
4765 explicit BoundValueRef( T& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4766
4767 ParserResult setValue( std::string const& arg ) override {
4768 return convertInto( arg, m_ref );
4769 }
4770 };
4771
4772 template <typename T>
4773 struct BoundValueRef<std::vector<T>> : BoundValueRefBase {
4774 std::vector<T>& m_ref;
4775
4776 explicit BoundValueRef( std::vector<T>& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4777
4778 auto isContainer() const -> bool override { return true; }
4779
4780 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4781 -> ParserResult override {
4782 T temp;
4783 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4784 if ( result )
4785 m_ref.push_back( temp );
4786 return result;
4787 }
4788 };
4789
4790 struct BoundFlagRef : BoundFlagRefBase {
4791 bool& m_ref;
4792
4793 explicit BoundFlagRef( bool& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4794
4795 ParserResult setFlag( bool flag ) override;
4796 };
4797
4798 template <typename ReturnType> struct LambdaInvoker {
4799 static_assert(
4800 std::is_same<ReturnType, ParserResult>::value,
4801 "Lambda must return void or clara::ParserResult" );
4802
4803 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4804 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4805 -> ParserResult {
4806 return lambda( arg );
4807 }
4808 };
4809
4810 template <> struct LambdaInvoker<void> {
4811 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4812 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4813 -> ParserResult {
4814 lambda( arg );
4815 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4816 }
4817 };
4818
4819 template <typename ArgType, typename L>
4820 auto invokeLambda( L const& lambda, std::string const& arg )
4821 -> ParserResult {
4822 ArgType temp{};
4823 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4824 return !result ? result
4825 : LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4826 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( lambda, temp );
4827 }
4828
4829 template <typename L> struct BoundLambda : BoundValueRefBase {
4830 L m_lambda;
4831
4832 static_assert(
4833 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4834 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4835 explicit BoundLambda( L const& lambda ): m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4836
4837 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4838 -> ParserResult override {
4839 return invokeLambda<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType>(
4840 m_lambda, arg );
4841 }
4842 };
4843
4844 template <typename L> struct BoundManyLambda : BoundLambda<L> {
4845 explicit BoundManyLambda( L const& lambda ): BoundLambda<L>( lambda ) {}
4846 bool isContainer() const override { return true; }
4847 };
4848
4849 template <typename L> struct BoundFlagLambda : BoundFlagRefBase {
4850 L m_lambda;
4851
4852 static_assert(
4853 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4854 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4855 static_assert(
4856 std::is_same<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType,
4857 bool>::value,
4858 "flags must be boolean" );
4859
4860 explicit BoundFlagLambda( L const& lambda ):
4861 m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4862
4863 auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult override {
4864 return LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4865 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( m_lambda, flag );
4866 }
4867 };
4868
4869 enum class Optionality { Optional, Required };
4870
4871 class ParserBase {
4872 public:
4873 virtual ~ParserBase() = default;
4874 virtual auto validate() const -> Result { return Result::ok(); }
4875 virtual auto parse( std::string const& exeName,
4876 TokenStream const& tokens ) const
4877 -> InternalParseResult = 0;
4878 virtual size_t cardinality() const;
4879
4880 InternalParseResult parse( Args const& args ) const;
4881 };
4882
4883 template <typename DerivedT>
4884 class ComposableParserImpl : public ParserBase {
4885 public:
4886 template <typename T>
4887 auto operator|( T const& other ) const -> Parser;
4888 };
4889
4890 // Common code and state for Args and Opts
4891 template <typename DerivedT>
4892 class ParserRefImpl : public ComposableParserImpl<DerivedT> {
4893 protected:
4894 Optionality m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4895 std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> m_ref;
4896 std::string m_hint;
4897 std::string m_description;
4898
4899 explicit ParserRefImpl( std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> const& ref ):
4900 m_ref( ref ) {}
4901
4902 public:
4903 template <typename LambdaT>
4904 ParserRefImpl( accept_many_t,
4905 LambdaT const& ref,
4906 std::string const& hint ):
4907 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundManyLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
4908 m_hint( hint ) {}
4909
4910 template <typename T,
4911 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
4912 !Detail::is_unary_function<T>::value>>
4913 ParserRefImpl( T& ref, std::string const& hint ):
4914 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundValueRef<T>>( ref ) ),
4915 m_hint( hint ) {}
4916
4917 template <typename LambdaT,
4918 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
4919 Detail::is_unary_function<LambdaT>::value>>
4920 ParserRefImpl( LambdaT const& ref, std::string const& hint ):
4921 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
4922 m_hint( hint ) {}
4923
4924 auto operator()( std::string const& description ) -> DerivedT& {
4925 m_description = description;
4926 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4927 }
4928
4929 auto optional() -> DerivedT& {
4930 m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4931 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4932 }
4933
4934 auto required() -> DerivedT& {
4935 m_optionality = Optionality::Required;
4936 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4937 }
4938
4939 auto isOptional() const -> bool {
4940 return m_optionality == Optionality::Optional;
4941 }
4942
4943 auto cardinality() const -> size_t override {
4944 if ( m_ref->isContainer() )
4945 return 0;
4946 else
4947 return 1;
4948 }
4949
4950 std::string const& hint() const { return m_hint; }
4951 };
4952
4953 } // namespace detail
4954
4955

4985
4986 template <typename LambdaT>

4988 ParserRefImpl( accept_many, ref, hint ) {}
4989
4990 template <typename T,
4991 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
4992 !Detail::is_unary_function<T>::value>>
4993 Opt( T& ref, std::string const& hint ):
4994 ParserRefImpl( ref, hint ) {}

5039 // A Combined parser
5040 class Parser : Detail::ParserBase {
5041 mutable ExeName m_exeName;
5042 std::vector<Opt> m_options;
5043 std::vector<Arg> m_args;
5044
5045 public:
5046
5047 auto operator|=(ExeName const& exeName) -> Parser& {
5048 m_exeName = exeName;
5049 return *this;
5050 }
5051
5052 auto operator|=(Arg const& arg) -> Parser& {
5053 m_args.push_back(arg);
5054 return *this;
5055 }
5056
5057 auto operator|=(Opt const& opt) -> Parser& {
5058 m_options.push_back(opt);
5059 return *this;
5060 }
5061
5062 Parser& operator|=(Parser const& other);
5063
5064 template <typename T>
5065 auto operator|(T const& other) const -> Parser {
5066 return Parser(*this) |= other;
5067 }
5068
5069 std::vector<Detail::HelpColumns> getHelpColumns() const;
5070
5071 void writeToStream(std::ostream& os) const;
5072
5073 friend auto operator<<(std::ostream& os, Parser const& parser)
5074 -> std::ostream& {
5075 parser.writeToStream(os);
5076 return os;
5077 }
5078
5079 Detail::Result validate() const override;
5080
5081 using ParserBase::parse;
5082 Detail::InternalParseResult
5083 parse(std::string const& exeName,
5084 Detail::TokenStream const& tokens) const override;
5085 };

5110 namespace Detail {
5111 template <typename DerivedT>
5112 template <typename T>
5113 Parser
5114 ComposableParserImpl<DerivedT>::operator|(T const& other) const {
5115 return Parser() | static_cast<DerivedT const&>(*this) | other;
5116 }
5117 }

5143
5144 class Session : Detail::NonCopyable {
5145 public:
5146
5147 Session();
5148 ~Session();
5149
5150 void showHelp() const;
5151 void libIdentify();
5152
5153 int applyCommandLine( int argc, char const * const * argv );
5154 #if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_WCHAR) && defined(_WIN32) && defined(UNICODE)
5155 int applyCommandLine( int argc, wchar_t const * const * argv );
5156 #endif
5157
5158 void useConfigData( ConfigData const& configData );
5159
5160 template<typename CharT>
5161 int run(int argc, CharT const * const argv[]) {
5162 if (m_startupExceptions)
5163 return 1;
5164 int returnCode = applyCommandLine(argc, argv);
5165 if (returnCode == 0)
5166 returnCode = run();
5167 return returnCode;
5168 }
5169
5170 int run();
5171
5172 Clara::Parser const& cli() const;
5173 void cli( Clara::Parser const& newParser );
5174 ConfigData& configData();
5175 Config& config();
5176 private:
5177 int runInternal();
5178
5179 Clara::Parser m_cli;
5180 ConfigData m_configData;
5181 Detail::unique_ptr<Config> m_config;
5182 bool m_startupExceptions = false;
5183 };

5268#ifndef CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED
5269#define CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED

5271
5272#include <type_traits>
