5274namespace Catch {
5275 namespace Detail {
5276
5277#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5278# pragma GCC diagnostic push
5279 // GCC likes to complain about comparing bool with 0, in the decltype()
5280 // that defines the comparable traits below.
5281# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wbool-compare"
5282 // "ordered comparison of pointer with integer zero" same as above,
5283 // but it does not have a separate warning flag to suppress
5284# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wextra"
5285 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5286 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5287# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5288#endif
5289
5290#if defined( __clang__ )
5291# pragma clang diagnostic push
5292 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5293 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5294# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5295#endif
5296
5297#define CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( id, op ) \
5298 template <typename, typename, typename = void> \
5299 struct is_##id##_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5300 template <typename T, typename U> \
5301 struct is_##id##_comparable< \
5302 T, \
5303 U, \
5304 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op std::declval<U>() )>> \
5305 : std::true_type {}; \
5306 template <typename, typename = void> \
5307 struct is_##id##_0_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5308 template <typename T> \
5309 struct is_##id##_0_comparable<T, \
5310 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op 0 )>> \
5311 : std::true_type {};
5312
5313 // We need all 6 pre-spaceship comparison ops: <, <=, >, >=, ==, !=
5314 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( lt, < )
5315 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( le, <= )
5316 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( gt, > )
5317 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ge, >= )
5318 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( eq, == )
5319 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ne, != )
5320
5321#undef CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT
5322
5323#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5324# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5325#endif
5326#if defined( __clang__ )
5327# pragma clang diagnostic pop
5328#endif
5329
5330
5331 } // namespace Detail
5332} // namespace Catch
5333
5334#endif // CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED

5344
5345#if defined( __cpp_lib_logical_traits ) && __cpp_lib_logical_traits >= 201510
5346
5347 using std::conjunction;
5348 using std::disjunction;
5349 using std::negation;
5350
5351#else
5352
5353 template <class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
5354 template <class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5355 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5356 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...>
5357 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), conjunction<Bn...>, B1> {};
5358
5359 template <class...> struct disjunction : std::false_type {};
5360 template <class B1> struct disjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5361 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5362 struct disjunction<B1, Bn...>
5363 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), B1, disjunction<Bn...>> {};
5364
5365 template <class B>
5366 struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, !bool(B::value)> {};
5367
5368#endif

5370} // namespace Detail

5399
5400 class ITransientExpression {
5401 bool m_isBinaryExpression;
5402 bool m_result;
5403
5404 public:
5405 auto isBinaryExpression() const -> bool { return m_isBinaryExpression; }
5406 auto getResult() const -> bool { return m_result; }
5407 virtual void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const = 0;
5408
5409 ITransientExpression( bool isBinaryExpression, bool result )
5410 : m_isBinaryExpression( isBinaryExpression ),
5411 m_result( result )
5412 {}
5413
5414 ITransientExpression() = default;
5415 ITransientExpression(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
5416 ITransientExpression& operator=(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
5417
5418 // We don't actually need a virtual destructor, but many static analysers
5419 // complain if it's not here :-(
5420 virtual ~ITransientExpression(); // = default;
5421
5422 friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out, ITransientExpression const& expr) {
5423 expr.streamReconstructedExpression(out);
5424 return out;
5425 }
5426 };
5427
5428 void formatReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os, std::string const& lhs, StringRef op, std::string const& rhs );
5429
5430 template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
5431 class BinaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
5432 LhsT m_lhs;
5433 StringRef m_op;
5434 RhsT m_rhs;
5435
5436 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
5437 formatReconstructedExpression
5438 ( os, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs ), m_op, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_rhs ) );
5439 }
5440
5441 public:
5442 BinaryExpr( bool comparisonResult, LhsT lhs, StringRef op, RhsT rhs )
5443 : ITransientExpression{ true, comparisonResult },
5444 m_lhs( lhs ),
5445 m_op( op ),
5446 m_rhs( rhs )
5447 {}
5448
5449 template<typename T>
5450 auto operator && ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5451 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5452 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5453 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5454 }
5455
5456 template<typename T>
5457 auto operator || ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5458 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5459 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5460 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5461 }
5462
5463 template<typename T>
5464 auto operator == ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5465 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5466 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5467 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5468 }
5469
5470 template<typename T>
5471 auto operator != ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5472 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5473 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5474 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5475 }
5476
5477 template<typename T>
5478 auto operator > ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5479 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5480 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5481 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5482 }
5483
5484 template<typename T>
5485 auto operator < ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5486 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5487 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5488 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5489 }
5490
5491 template<typename T>
5492 auto operator >= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5493 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5494 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5495 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5496 }
5497
5498 template<typename T>
5499 auto operator <= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5500 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5501 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5502 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5503 }
5504 };
5505
5506 template<typename LhsT>
5507 class UnaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
5508 LhsT m_lhs;
5509
5510 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
5511 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs );
5512 }
5513
5514 public:
5515 explicit UnaryExpr( LhsT lhs )
5516 : ITransientExpression{ false, static_cast<bool>(lhs) },
5517 m_lhs( lhs )
5518 {}
5519 };

5521
5522 template<typename LhsT>
5523 class ExprLhs {
5524 LhsT m_lhs;
5525 public:
5526 explicit ExprLhs( LhsT lhs ) : m_lhs( lhs ) {}
5527
5528#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( id, op ) \
5529 template <typename RhsT> \
5530 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5531 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5532 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5533 Detail::negation<std::is_arithmetic< \
5534 std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>>>::value, \
5535 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5536 return { \
5537 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5538 } \
5539 template <typename RhsT> \
5540 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5541 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5542 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5543 std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>>::value, \
5544 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5545 return { \
5546 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5547 } \
5548 template <typename RhsT> \
5549 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5550 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5551 Detail::conjunction< \
5552 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5553 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<LhsT>, \
5554 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5555 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<RhsT, int>, \
5556 std::is_same<RhsT, long>>>::value, \
5557 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5558 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5559 return { \
5560 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5561 } \
5562 template <typename RhsT> \
5563 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5564 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5565 Detail::conjunction< \
5566 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5567 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5568 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5569 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<LhsT, int>, \
5570 std::is_same<LhsT, long>>>::value, \
5571 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5572 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5573 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5574 }
5575
5576 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( eq, == )
5577 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( ne, != )
5578
5579 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR
5580
5581#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( id, op ) \
5582 template <typename RhsT> \
5583 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5584 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5585 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5586 Detail::negation<std::is_arithmetic< \
5587 std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>>>::value, \
5588 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5589 return { \
5590 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5591 } \
5592 template <typename RhsT> \
5593 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5594 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5595 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5596 std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>>::value, \
5597 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5598 return { \
5599 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5600 } \
5601 template <typename RhsT> \
5602 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5603 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5604 Detail::conjunction< \
5605 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5606 Detail::is_##id##_0_comparable<LhsT>, \
5607 std::is_same<RhsT, int>>::value, \
5608 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5609 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5610 return { \
5611 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5612 } \
5613 template <typename RhsT> \
5614 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5615 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5616 Detail::conjunction< \
5617 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5618 Detail::is_##id##_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5619 std::is_same<LhsT, int>>::value, \
5620 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5621 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5622 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5623 }
5624
5625 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( lt, < )
5626 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( le, <= )
5627 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( gt, > )
5628 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( ge, >= )
5629
5630 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR
5631
5632
5633#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR( op ) \
5634 template <typename RhsT> \
5635 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5636 ->std::enable_if_t< \
5637 !std::is_arithmetic<std::remove_reference_t<RhsT>>::value, \
5638 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5639 return { \
5640 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5641 } \
5642 template <typename RhsT> \
5643 friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5644 ->std::enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<RhsT>::value, \
5645 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5646 return { \
5647 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5648 }
5649
5650 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(|)
5651 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(&)
5652 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(^)
5653
5654 #undef CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR
5655
5656 template<typename RhsT>
5657 friend auto operator && ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5658 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5659 "operator&& is not supported inside assertions, "
5660 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5661 }
5662
5663 template<typename RhsT>
5664 friend auto operator || ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5665 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5666 "operator|| is not supported inside assertions, "
5667 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5668 }
5669
5670 auto makeUnaryExpr() const -> UnaryExpr<LhsT> {
5671 return UnaryExpr<LhsT>{ m_lhs };
5672 }
5673 };
5674
5675 struct Decomposer {
5676 template<typename T, std::enable_if_t<!std::is_arithmetic<std::remove_reference_t<T>>::value, int> = 0>
5677 friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T && lhs ) -> ExprLhs<T const&> {
5678 return ExprLhs<const T&>{ lhs };
5679 }
5680
5681 template<typename T, std::enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<T>::value, int> = 0>
5682 friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T value ) -> ExprLhs<T> {
5683 return ExprLhs<T>{ value };
5684 }
5685 };

5704 struct AssertionReaction {
5705 bool shouldDebugBreak = false;
5706 bool shouldThrow = false;
5707 bool shouldSkip = false;
5708 };
5709
5710 class AssertionHandler {
5711 AssertionInfo m_assertionInfo;
5712 AssertionReaction m_reaction;
5713 bool m_completed = false;
5714 IResultCapture& m_resultCapture;
5715
5716 public:
5717 AssertionHandler
5718 ( StringRef macroName,
5719 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo,
5720 StringRef capturedExpression,
5721 ResultDisposition::Flags resultDisposition );
5722 ~AssertionHandler() {
5723 if ( !m_completed ) {
5724 m_resultCapture.handleIncomplete( m_assertionInfo );
5725 }
5726 }
5727
5728
5729 template<typename T>
5730 void handleExpr( ExprLhs<T> const& expr ) {
5731 handleExpr( expr.makeUnaryExpr() );
5732 }
5733 void handleExpr( ITransientExpression const& expr );
5734
5735 void handleMessage(ResultWas::OfType resultType, StringRef message);
5736
5737 void handleExceptionThrownAsExpected();
5738 void handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown();
5739 void handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected();
5740 void handleThrowingCallSkipped();
5741 void handleUnexpectedInflightException();
5742
5743 void complete();
5744
5745 // query
5746 auto allowThrows() const -> bool;
5747 };
5748
5749 void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, std::string const& str );

5751} // namespace Catch

5756#ifndef CATCH_PREPROCESSOR_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY_HPP_INCLUDED
5757#define CATCH_PREPROCESSOR_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY_HPP_INCLUDED
5758
5759
5760#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION)
5761 #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) #__VA_ARGS__##_catch_sr
5762#else
5763 #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) "Disabled by CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION"_catch_sr
5764#endif
5765
5766#endif // CATCH_PREPROCESSOR_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY_HPP_INCLUDED
5767
5768// We need this suppression to leak, because it took until GCC 10
5769// for the front end to handle local suppression via _Pragma properly
5770#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && !defined(__ICC) && __GNUC__ <= 9
5771 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wparentheses"
5772#endif
5773
5774#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
5775
5776#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE) || defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
5777
5779// Another way to speed-up compilation is to omit local try-catch for REQUIRE*
5780// macros.
5781#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY
5782#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( capturer )
5783
5784#else // CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE
5785
5786#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY try
5787#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( handler ) catch(...) { handler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); }
5788
5789#endif
5790
5791#define INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( handler ) handler.complete();
5792
5794#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5795 do { /* NOLINT(bugprone-infinite-loop) */ \
5796 /* The expression should not be evaluated, but warnings should hopefully be checked */ \
5797 CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(__VA_ARGS__); \
5798 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5799 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
5800 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5801 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
5802 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::Decomposer() <= __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5803 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5804 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5805 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5806 } while( (void)0, (false) && static_cast<const bool&>( !!(__VA_ARGS__) ) ) // the expression here is never evaluated at runtime but it forces the compiler to give it a look
5807 // The double negation silences MSVC's C4800 warning, the static_cast forces short-circuit evaluation if the type has overloaded &&.
5808
5810#define INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5811 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5812 if( Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5813
5815#define INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5816 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5817 if( !Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5818
5820#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5821 do { \
5822 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5823 try { \
5824 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5825 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5826 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5827 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5828 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected(); \
5829 } \
5830 catch( ... ) { \
5831 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5832 } \
5833 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5834 } while( false )
5835
5837#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5838 do { \
5839 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition); \
5840 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5841 try { \
5842 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5843 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5844 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5845 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5846 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5847 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5848 } \
5849 catch( ... ) { \
5850 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5851 } \
5852 else \
5853 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5854 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5855 } while( false )
5856
5858#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, expr ) \
5859 do { \
5860 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(expr) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType), resultDisposition ); \
5861 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5862 try { \
5863 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5864 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5865 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5866 static_cast<void>(expr); \
5867 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5868 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5869 } \
5870 catch( exceptionType const& ) { \
5871 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5872 } \
5873 catch( ... ) { \
5874 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5875 } \
5876 else \
5877 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5878 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5879 } while( false )
5880
5881
5882
5884// Although this is matcher-based, it can be used with just a string
5885#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_STR_MATCHES( macroName, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
5886 do { \
5887 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
5888 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5889 try { \
5890 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5891 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5892 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5893 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5894 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5895 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5896 } \
5897 catch( ... ) { \
5898 Catch::handleExceptionMatchExpr( catchAssertionHandler, matcher ); \
5899 } \
5900 else \
5901 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5902 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5903 } while( false )
5904
5905#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE
5906
5907#endif // CATCH_TEST_MACRO_IMPL_HPP_INCLUDED

6091namespace Catch {
6092
6093template<typename C>
6094class TestInvokerAsMethod : public ITestInvoker {
6095 void (C::*m_testAsMethod)();
6096public:
6097 TestInvokerAsMethod( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) noexcept : m_testAsMethod( testAsMethod ) {}
6098
6099 void invoke() const override {
6100 C obj;
6101 (obj.*m_testAsMethod)();
6102 }
6103};
6104
6105Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void(*testAsFunction)() );
6106
6107template<typename C>
6108Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) {
6109 return Detail::make_unique<TestInvokerAsMethod<C>>( testAsMethod );
6110}
6111
6112struct NameAndTags {
6113 constexpr NameAndTags( StringRef name_ = StringRef(),
6114 StringRef tags_ = StringRef() ) noexcept:
6115 name( name_ ), tags( tags_ ) {}
6116 StringRef name;
6117 StringRef tags;
6118};
6119
6120struct AutoReg : Detail::NonCopyable {
6121 AutoReg( Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> invoker, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, StringRef classOrMethod, NameAndTags const& nameAndTags ) noexcept;
6122};
6123
6124} // end namespace Catch

6238// All of our user-facing macros support configuration toggle, that
6239// forces them to be defined prefixed with CATCH_. We also like to
6240// support another toggle that can minimize (disable) their implementation.
6241// Given this, we have 4 different configuration options below

6250 #define CATCH_REQUIRE_NOTHROW( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( "CATCH_REQUIRE_NOTHROW", Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ )
6251
6252 #define CATCH_CHECK( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_CHECK", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6253 #define CATCH_CHECK_FALSE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_CHECK_FALSE", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::FalseTest, __VA_ARGS__ )
6254 #define CATCH_CHECKED_IF( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( "CATCH_CHECKED_IF", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::SuppressFail, __VA_ARGS__ )
6255 #define CATCH_CHECKED_ELSE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( "CATCH_CHECKED_ELSE", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::SuppressFail, __VA_ARGS__ )

6482#define CATCH_EMPTY()

6485#define CATCH_REC_GET_END2() 0, CATCH_REC_END
6486#define CATCH_REC_GET_END1(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END2
6487#define CATCH_REC_GET_END(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END1
6488#define CATCH_REC_NEXT0(test, next, ...) next CATCH_REC_OUT
6489#define CATCH_REC_NEXT1(test, next) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT0 ) ( test, next, 0)
6490#define CATCH_REC_NEXT(test, next) CATCH_REC_NEXT1(CATCH_REC_GET_END test, next)
6491
6492#define CATCH_REC_LIST0(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6493#define CATCH_REC_LIST1(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6494#define CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, x, peek, ...) f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6495
6496#define CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6497#define CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6498#define CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6499
6500// Applies the function macro `f` to each of the remaining parameters, inserts commas between the results,
6501// and passes userdata as the first parameter to each invocation,
6502// e.g. CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, x, a, b, c) evaluates to f(x, a), f(x, b), f(x, c)
6503#define CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, userdata, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))
6504
6505#define CATCH_REC_LIST(f, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))

6510#define INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS(param) INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(param))
6511#else
6512// MSVC is adding extra space and needs another indirection to expand INTERNAL_CATCH_NOINTERNAL_CATCH_DEF

6514#define INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE3(...) #__VA_ARGS__
6515#define INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS(param) (INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(param)) + 1)
6516#endif

6546#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN\
6547 template<typename...> struct TypeList {};\
6548 template<typename...Ts>\
6549 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TypeList<Ts...> { return {}; }\
6550 template<template<typename...> class...> struct TemplateTypeList{};\
6551 template<template<typename...> class...Cs>\
6552 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; }\
6553 template<typename...>\
6554 struct append;\
6555 template<typename...>\
6556 struct rewrap;\
6557 template<template<typename...> class, typename...>\
6558 struct create;\
6559 template<template<typename...> class, typename>\
6560 struct convert;\
6561 \
6562 template<typename T> \
6563 struct append<T> { using type = T; };\
6564 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, template<typename...> class L2, typename...E2, typename...Rest>\
6565 struct append<L1<E1...>, L2<E2...>, Rest...> { using type = typename append<L1<E1...,E2...>, Rest...>::type; };\
6566 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, typename...Rest>\
6567 struct append<L1<E1...>, TypeList<mpl_::na>, Rest...> { using type = L1<E1...>; };\
6568 \
6569 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, typename...elems>\
6570 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<elems...>> { using type = TypeList<Container<elems...>>; };\
6571 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, class...Elems, typename...Elements>\
6572 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<Elems...>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<Elems...>>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6573 \
6574 template<template <typename...> class Final, template< typename...> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
6575 struct create<Final, TemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };\
6576 template<template <typename...> class Final, template <typename...> class List, typename...Ts>\
6577 struct convert<Final, List<Ts...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>,TypeList<Ts>...>::type; };
6578
6579#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_1(signature, ...)\
6580 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> struct Nttp{};\
6581 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6582 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> Nttp<__VA_ARGS__> { return {}; } \
6583 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...> struct NttpTemplateTypeList{};\
6584 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Cs>\
6585 constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> NttpTemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; } \
6586 \
6587 template< template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class Container, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class List, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6588 struct rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, List<__VA_ARGS__>> { using type = TypeList<Container<__VA_ARGS__>>; };\
6589 template< template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class Container, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class List, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature), typename...Elements>\
6590 struct rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, List<__VA_ARGS__>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<__VA_ARGS__>>, typename rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6591 template<template <typename...> class Final, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
6592 struct create<Final, NttpTemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };

6784 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEMPLATE_PRODUCT_TEST_CASE2(TestName, TestFuncName, Name, Tags, Signature, TmplTypes, TypesList) \
6785 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6786 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6787 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \
6788 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_WARNINGS \
6789 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
6790 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_COMMA_WARNINGS \
6791 template<typename TestType> static void TestFuncName(); \
6792 namespace {\
6793 namespace INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_NAMESPACE(TestName) { \
6794 INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN \
6795 INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_GEN(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature)) \
6796 template<typename... Types> \
6797 struct TestName { \
6798 void reg_tests() { \
6799 size_t index = 0; \
6800 using expander = size_t[]; \
6801 constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes))};\
6802 constexpr char const* types_list[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))};\
6803 constexpr auto num_types = sizeof(types_list) / sizeof(types_list[0]);\
6804 (void)expander{(Catch::AutoReg( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestFuncName<Types> ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index / num_types]) + '<' + std::string(types_list[index % num_types]) + '>', Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */\
6805 } \
6806 }; \
6807 static int INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( globalRegistrar ) = [](){ \
6808 using TestInit = typename create<TestName, decltype(get_wrapper<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes)>()), TypeList<INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_TYPE_LISTS_FROM_TYPES(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))>>::type; \
6809 TestInit t; \
6810 t.reg_tests(); \
6811 return 0; \
6812 }(); \
6813 } \
6814 } \
6815 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6816 template<typename TestType> \

7265namespace Catch {
7266 namespace Detail {
7267 void registerTranslatorImpl(
7268 Detail::unique_ptr<IExceptionTranslator>&& translator );
7269 }
7270
7271 class ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar {
7272 template<typename T>
7273 class ExceptionTranslator : public IExceptionTranslator {
7274 public:
7275
7276 ExceptionTranslator( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) )
7277 : m_translateFunction( translateFunction )
7278 {}
7279
7280 std::string translate( ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator it, ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator itEnd ) const override {
7281#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
7282 try {
7283 if( it == itEnd )
7284 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
7285 else
7286 return (*it)->translate( it+1, itEnd );
7287 }
7288 catch( T const& ex ) {
7289 return m_translateFunction( ex );
7290 }
7291#else
7292 return "You should never get here!";
7293#endif
7294 }
7295
7296 protected:
7297 std::string(*m_translateFunction)( T const& );
7298 };
7299
7300 public:
7301 template<typename T>
7302 ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) ) {
7303 Detail::registerTranslatorImpl(
7304 Detail::make_unique<ExceptionTranslator<T>>(
7305 translateFunction ) );
7306 }
7307 };
7308
7309} // namespace Catch

7314 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7315 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
7316 namespace{ Catch::ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionRegistrar )( &translatorName ); } \
7317 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7318 static std::string translatorName( signature )
7319
7320#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION2( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionTranslator ), signature )
7321
7322#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
7323 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION_NO_REG( translatorName, signature) \

7325#endif

7529 template<typename T>
7530 class IGenerator : public GeneratorUntypedBase {
7531 std::string stringifyImpl() const override {
7532 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify( get() );
7533 }
7534
7535 public:
7536 ~IGenerator() override = default;
7537 IGenerator() = default;
7538 IGenerator(IGenerator const&) = default;
7539 IGenerator& operator=(IGenerator const&) = default;
7540
7541
7542 // Returns the current element of the generator
7543 //
7544 // \Precondition The generator is either freshly constructed,
7545 // or the last call to `next()` returned true
7546 virtual T const& get() const = 0;
7547 using type = T;
7548 };

7550 template <typename T>
7551 using GeneratorPtr = Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<IGenerator<T>>;
7552
7553 template <typename T>
7554 class GeneratorWrapper final {
7555 GeneratorPtr<T> m_generator;
7556 public:
7558 GeneratorWrapper(IGenerator<T>* generator):
7559 m_generator(generator) {}
7560 GeneratorWrapper(GeneratorPtr<T> generator):
7561 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)) {}
7562
7563 T const& get() const {
7564 return m_generator->get();
7565 }
7566 bool next() {
7567 return m_generator->countedNext();
7568 }
7569 };

7573 class SingleValueGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7574 T m_value;
7575 public:
7576 SingleValueGenerator(T const& value) :
7577 m_value(value)
7578 {}
7579 SingleValueGenerator(T&& value):
7580 m_value(CATCH_MOVE(value))
7581 {}
7582
7583 T const& get() const override {
7584 return m_value;
7585 }
7586 bool next() override {
7587 return false;
7588 }
7589 };

7591 template<typename T>
7592 class FixedValuesGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7593 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7594 "FixedValuesGenerator does not support bools because of std::vector<bool>"
7595 "specialization, use SingleValue Generator instead.");
7596 std::vector<T> m_values;
7597 size_t m_idx = 0;
7598 public:
7599 FixedValuesGenerator( std::initializer_list<T> values ) : m_values( values ) {}
7600
7601 T const& get() const override {
7602 return m_values[m_idx];
7603 }
7604 bool next() override {
7605 ++m_idx;
7606 return m_idx < m_values.size();
7607 }
7608 };

7610 template <typename T, typename DecayedT = std::decay_t<T>>
7611 GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT> value( T&& value ) {
7612 return GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT>(
7613 Catch::Detail::make_unique<SingleValueGenerator<DecayedT>>(
7614 CATCH_FORWARD( value ) ) );
7615 }
7616 template <typename T>
7617 GeneratorWrapper<T> values(std::initializer_list<T> values) {
7618 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FixedValuesGenerator<T>>(values));
7619 }
7620
7621 template<typename T>
7622 class Generators : public IGenerator<T> {
7623 std::vector<GeneratorWrapper<T>> m_generators;
7624 size_t m_current = 0;
7625
7626 void add_generator( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) {
7627 m_generators.emplace_back( CATCH_MOVE( generator ) );
7628 }
7629 void add_generator( T const& val ) {
7630 m_generators.emplace_back( value( val ) );
7631 }
7632 void add_generator( T&& val ) {
7633 m_generators.emplace_back( value( CATCH_MOVE( val ) ) );
7634 }
7635 template <typename U>
7636 std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<std::decay_t<U>, T>::value>
7637 add_generator( U&& val ) {
7638 add_generator( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) );
7639 }
7640
7641 template <typename U> void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator ) {
7642 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7643 }
7644
7645 template <typename U, typename... Gs>
7646 void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator, Gs&&... moreGenerators ) {
7647 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7648 add_generators( CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7649 }
7650
7651 public:
7652 template <typename... Gs>
7653 Generators(Gs &&... moreGenerators) {
7654 m_generators.reserve(sizeof...(Gs));
7655 add_generators(CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7656 }
7657
7658 T const& get() const override {
7659 return m_generators[m_current].get();
7660 }
7661
7662 bool next() override {
7663 if (m_current >= m_generators.size()) {
7664 return false;
7665 }
7666 const bool current_status = m_generators[m_current].next();
7667 if (!current_status) {
7668 ++m_current;
7669 }
7670 return m_current < m_generators.size();
7671 }
7672 };
7673
7674
7675 template <typename... Ts>
7676 GeneratorWrapper<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>>
7677 table( std::initializer_list<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>> tuples ) {
7678 return values<std::tuple<Ts...>>( tuples );
7679 }
7680
7681 // Tag type to signal that a generator sequence should convert arguments to a specific type
7682 template <typename T>
7683 struct as {};
7684
7685 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7686 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7687 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator), CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7688 }
7689 template<typename T>
7690 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) -> Generators<T> {
7691 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator));
7692 }
7693 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7694 auto makeGenerators( T&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<std::decay_t<T>> {
7695 return makeGenerators( value( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7696 }
7697 template<typename T, typename U, typename... Gs>
7698 auto makeGenerators( as<T>, U&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7699 return makeGenerators( value( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7700 }
7701
7702 IGeneratorTracker* acquireGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7703 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo );
7704 IGeneratorTracker* createGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7705 SourceLineInfo lineInfo,
7706 GeneratorBasePtr&& generator );
7707
7708 template<typename L>
7709 auto generate( StringRef generatorName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, L const& generatorExpression ) -> typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type {
7710 using UnderlyingType = typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type;
7711
7712 IGeneratorTracker* tracker = acquireGeneratorTracker( generatorName, lineInfo );
7713 // Creation of tracker is delayed after generator creation, so
7714 // that constructing generator can fail without breaking everything.
7715 if (!tracker) {
7716 tracker = createGeneratorTracker(
7717 generatorName,
7718 lineInfo,
7719 Catch::Detail::make_unique<Generators<UnderlyingType>>(
7720 generatorExpression() ) );
7721 }
7722
7723 auto const& generator = static_cast<IGenerator<UnderlyingType> const&>( *tracker->getGenerator() );
7724 return generator.get();
7725 }

7731#define CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(...) CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE_IMPL(__VA_ARGS__)
7732
7733#define GENERATE( ... ) \
7734 Catch::Generators::generate( CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7735 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7736 [ ]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7737#define GENERATE_COPY( ... ) \

7739 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7740 [=]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7741#define GENERATE_REF( ... ) \
7742 Catch::Generators::generate( CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7743 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7744 [&]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)

7749#ifndef CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7750#define CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7751
7752
7753#include <cassert>
7754
7755namespace Catch {
7756namespace Generators {
7757
7758 template <typename T>
7759 class TakeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7760 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7761 size_t m_returned = 0;
7762 size_t m_target;
7763 public:
7764 TakeGenerator(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7765 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7766 m_target(target)
7767 {
7768 assert(target != 0 && "Empty generators are not allowed");
7769 }
7770 T const& get() const override {
7771 return m_generator.get();
7772 }
7773 bool next() override {
7774 ++m_returned;
7775 if (m_returned >= m_target) {
7776 return false;
7777 }
7778
7779 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7780 // If the underlying generator does not contain enough values
7781 // then we cut short as well
7782 if (!success) {
7783 m_returned = m_target;
7784 }
7785 return success;
7786 }
7787 };
7788
7789 template <typename T>
7790 GeneratorWrapper<T> take(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7791 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<TakeGenerator<T>>(target, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7792 }
7793
7794
7795 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7796 class FilterGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7797 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7798 Predicate m_predicate;
7799 public:
7800 template <typename P = Predicate>
7801 FilterGenerator(P&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7802 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7803 m_predicate(CATCH_FORWARD(pred))
7804 {
7805 if (!m_predicate(m_generator.get())) {
7806 // It might happen that there are no values that pass the
7807 // filter. In that case we throw an exception.
7808 auto has_initial_value = next();
7809 if (!has_initial_value) {
7810 Detail::throw_generator_exception("No valid value found in filtered generator");
7811 }
7812 }
7813 }
7814
7815 T const& get() const override {
7816 return m_generator.get();
7817 }
7818
7819 bool next() override {
7820 bool success = m_generator.next();
7821 if (!success) {
7822 return false;
7823 }
7824 while (!m_predicate(m_generator.get()) && (success = m_generator.next()) == true);
7825 return success;
7826 }
7827 };
7828
7829
7830 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7831 GeneratorWrapper<T> filter(Predicate&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7832 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FilterGenerator<T, Predicate>>(CATCH_FORWARD(pred), CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7833 }
7834
7835 template <typename T>
7836 class RepeatGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7837 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7838 "RepeatGenerator currently does not support bools"
7839 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
7840 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7841 mutable std::vector<T> m_returned;
7842 size_t m_target_repeats;
7843 size_t m_current_repeat = 0;
7844 size_t m_repeat_index = 0;
7845 public:
7846 RepeatGenerator(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7847 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7848 m_target_repeats(repeats)
7849 {
7850 assert(m_target_repeats > 0 && "Repeat generator must repeat at least once");
7851 }
7852
7853 T const& get() const override {
7854 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7855 m_returned.push_back(m_generator.get());
7856 return m_returned.back();
7857 }
7858 return m_returned[m_repeat_index];
7859 }
7860
7861 bool next() override {
7862 // There are 2 basic cases:
7863 // 1) We are still reading the generator
7864 // 2) We are reading our own cache
7865
7866 // In the first case, we need to poke the underlying generator.
7867 // If it happily moves, we are left in that state, otherwise it is time to start reading from our cache
7868 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7869 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7870 if (!success) {
7871 ++m_current_repeat;
7872 }
7873 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7874 }
7875
7876 // In the second case, we need to move indices forward and check that we haven't run up against the end
7877 ++m_repeat_index;
7878 if (m_repeat_index == m_returned.size()) {
7879 m_repeat_index = 0;
7880 ++m_current_repeat;
7881 }
7882 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7883 }
7884 };
7885
7886 template <typename T>
7887 GeneratorWrapper<T> repeat(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7888 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RepeatGenerator<T>>(repeats, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7889 }
7890
7891 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7892 class MapGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7893 // TBD: provide static assert for mapping function, for friendly error message
7894 GeneratorWrapper<U> m_generator;
7895 Func m_function;
7896 // To avoid returning dangling reference, we have to save the values
7897 T m_cache;
7898 public:
7899 template <typename F2 = Func>
7900 MapGenerator(F2&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) :
7901 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7902 m_function(CATCH_FORWARD(function)),
7903 m_cache(m_function(m_generator.get()))
7904 {}
7905
7906 T const& get() const override {
7907 return m_cache;
7908 }
7909 bool next() override {
7910 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7911 if (success) {
7912 m_cache = m_function(m_generator.get());
7913 }
7914 return success;
7915 }
7916 };
7917
7918 template <typename Func, typename U, typename T = FunctionReturnType<Func, U>>
7919 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
7920 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7921 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7922 );
7923 }
7924
7925 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7926 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
7927 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7928 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7929 );
7930 }
7931
7932 template <typename T>
7933 class ChunkGenerator final : public IGenerator<std::vector<T>> {
7934 std::vector<T> m_chunk;
7935 size_t m_chunk_size;
7936 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7937 bool m_used_up = false;
7938 public:
7939 ChunkGenerator(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T> generator) :
7940 m_chunk_size(size), m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7941 {
7942 m_chunk.reserve(m_chunk_size);
7943 if (m_chunk_size != 0) {
7944 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7945 for (size_t i = 1; i < m_chunk_size; ++i) {
7946 if (!m_generator.next()) {
7947 Detail::throw_generator_exception("Not enough values to initialize the first chunk");
7948 }
7949 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7950 }
7951 }
7952 }
7953 std::vector<T> const& get() const override {
7954 return m_chunk;
7955 }
7956 bool next() override {
7957 m_chunk.clear();
7958 for (size_t idx = 0; idx < m_chunk_size; ++idx) {
7959 if (!m_generator.next()) {
7960 return false;
7961 }
7962 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7963 }
7964 return true;
7965 }
7966 };
7967
7968 template <typename T>
7969 GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>> chunk(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7970 return GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>>(
7971 Catch::Detail::make_unique<ChunkGenerator<T>>(size, CATCH_MOVE(generator))
7972 );
7973 }

7987#ifndef CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
7988#define CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
7989
7990#include <cstdint>
7991
7992namespace Catch {
7993
7994 // This is a simple implementation of C++11 Uniform Random Number
7995 // Generator. It does not provide all operators, because Catch2
7996 // does not use it, but it should behave as expected inside stdlib's
7997 // distributions.
7998 // The implementation is based on the PCG family (http://pcg-random.org)
7999 class SimplePcg32 {
8000 using state_type = std::uint64_t;
8001 public:
8002 using result_type = std::uint32_t;
8003 static constexpr result_type (min)() {
8004 return 0;
8005 }
8006 static constexpr result_type (max)() {
8007 return static_cast<result_type>(-1);
8008 }
8009
8010 // Provide some default initial state for the default constructor
8011 SimplePcg32():SimplePcg32(0xed743cc4U) {}
8012
8013 explicit SimplePcg32(result_type seed_);
8014
8015 void seed(result_type seed_);
8016 void discard(uint64_t skip);
8017
8018 result_type operator()();
8019
8020 private:
8021 friend bool operator==(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8022 friend bool operator!=(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8023
8024 // In theory we also need operator<< and operator>>
8025 // In practice we do not use them, so we will skip them for now
8026
8027
8028 std::uint64_t m_state;
8029 // This part of the state determines which "stream" of the numbers
8030 // is chosen -- we take it as a constant for Catch2, so we only
8031 // need to deal with seeding the main state.
8032 // Picked by reading 8 bytes from `/dev/random` :-)
8033 static const std::uint64_t s_inc = (0x13ed0cc53f939476ULL << 1ULL) | 1ULL;
8034 };
8035
8036} // end namespace Catch
8037
8038#endif // CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
8039
8040#include <random>
8041
8042namespace Catch {
8043namespace Generators {
8044namespace Detail {
8045 // Returns a suitable seed for a random floating generator based off
8046 // the primary internal rng. It does so by taking current value from
8047 // the rng and returning it as the seed.
8048 std::uint32_t getSeed();
8049}
8050
8051template <typename Float>
8052class RandomFloatingGenerator final : public IGenerator<Float> {
8053 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8054 std::uniform_real_distribution<Float> m_dist;
8055 Float m_current_number;
8056public:
8057 RandomFloatingGenerator( Float a, Float b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8058 m_rng(seed),
8059 m_dist(a, b) {
8060 static_cast<void>(next());
8061 }
8062
8063 Float const& get() const override {
8064 return m_current_number;
8065 }
8066 bool next() override {
8067 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8068 return true;
8069 }
8070};
8071
8072template <typename Integer>
8073class RandomIntegerGenerator final : public IGenerator<Integer> {
8074 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8075 std::uniform_int_distribution<Integer> m_dist;
8076 Integer m_current_number;
8077public:
8078 RandomIntegerGenerator( Integer a, Integer b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8079 m_rng(seed),
8080 m_dist(a, b) {
8081 static_cast<void>(next());
8082 }
8083
8084 Integer const& get() const override {
8085 return m_current_number;
8086 }
8087 bool next() override {
8088 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8089 return true;
8090 }
8091};
8092
8093template <typename T>
8094std::enable_if_t<std::is_integral<T>::value, GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8095random(T a, T b) {
8096 static_assert(
8097 !std::is_same<T, char>::value &&
8098 !std::is_same<T, int8_t>::value &&
8099 !std::is_same<T, uint8_t>::value &&
8100 !std::is_same<T, signed char>::value &&
8101 !std::is_same<T, unsigned char>::value &&
8102 !std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
8103 "The requested type is not supported by the underlying random distributions from std" );
8104 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8105 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomIntegerGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8106 );
8107}
8108
8109template <typename T>
8110std::enable_if_t<std::is_floating_point<T>::value,
8111GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8112random(T a, T b) {
8113 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8114 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomFloatingGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8115 );
8116}

8136
8137template <typename T>
8138class RangeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8139 T m_current;
8140 T m_end;
8141 T m_step;
8142 bool m_positive;
8143
8144public:
8145 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step):
8146 m_current(start),
8147 m_end(end),
8148 m_step(step),
8149 m_positive(m_step > T(0))
8150 {
8151 assert(m_current != m_end && "Range start and end cannot be equal");
8152 assert(m_step != T(0) && "Step size cannot be zero");
8153 assert(((m_positive && m_current <= m_end) || (!m_positive && m_current >= m_end)) && "Step moves away from end");
8154 }
8155
8156 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end):
8157 RangeGenerator(start, end, (start < end) ? T(1) : T(-1))
8158 {}
8159
8160 T const& get() const override {
8161 return m_current;
8162 }
8163
8164 bool next() override {
8165 m_current += m_step;
8166 return (m_positive) ? (m_current < m_end) : (m_current > m_end);
8167 }
8168};
8169
8170template <typename T>
8171GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step) {
8172 static_assert(std::is_arithmetic<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be numeric");
8173 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end, step));
8174}
8175
8176template <typename T>
8177GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end) {
8178 static_assert(std::is_integral<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be an integer");
8179 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end));
8180}
8181
8182
8183template <typename T>
8184class IteratorGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8185 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
8186 "IteratorGenerator currently does not support bools"
8187 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
8188
8189 std::vector<T> m_elems;
8190 size_t m_current = 0;
8191public:
8192 template <typename InputIterator, typename InputSentinel>
8193 IteratorGenerator(InputIterator first, InputSentinel last):m_elems(first, last) {
8194 if (m_elems.empty()) {
8195 Detail::throw_generator_exception("IteratorGenerator received no valid values");
8196 }
8197 }
8198
8199 T const& get() const override {
8200 return m_elems[m_current];
8201 }
8202
8203 bool next() override {
8204 ++m_current;
8205 return m_current != m_elems.size();
8206 }
8207};
8208
8209template <typename InputIterator,
8210 typename InputSentinel,
8211 typename ResultType = typename std::iterator_traits<InputIterator>::value_type>
8212GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(InputIterator from, InputSentinel to) {
8213 return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(from, to));
8214}
8215
8216template <typename Container,
8217 typename ResultType = typename Container::value_type>
8218GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(Container const& cnt) {
8219 return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(cnt.begin(), cnt.end()));
8220}

8677// We want a simple polyfill over `std::empty`, `std::size` and so on
8678// for C++14 or C++ libraries with incomplete support.
8679// We also have to handle that MSVC std lib will happily provide these
8680// under older standards.
8681#if defined(CATCH_CPP17_OR_GREATER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
8682
8683// We are already using this header either way, so there shouldn't
8684// be much additional overhead in including it to get the feature
8685// test macros
8686#include <string>

8688# if !defined(__cpp_lib_nonmember_container_access)
8689# define CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS

8694#endif

8698namespace Catch {
8699namespace Detail {
8700
8701#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
8702 template <typename Container>
8703 constexpr auto empty(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.empty()) {
8704 return cont.empty();
8705 }
8706 template <typename T, std::size_t N>
8707 constexpr bool empty(const T (&)[N]) noexcept {
8708 // GCC < 7 does not support the const T(&)[] parameter syntax
8709 // so we have to ignore the length explicitly
8710 (void)N;
8711 return false;
8712 }
8713 template <typename T>
8714 constexpr bool empty(std::initializer_list<T> list) noexcept {
8715 return list.size() > 0;
8716 }
8717
8718
8719 template <typename Container>
8720 constexpr auto size(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.size()) {
8721 return cont.size();
8722 }
8723 template <typename T, std::size_t N>
8724 constexpr std::size_t size(const T(&)[N]) noexcept {
8725 return N;
8726 }
8727#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS

8757#ifdef CATCH_PLATFORM_MAC
8758
8759 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
8760 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3\n" : : ) /* NOLINT */
8761 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
8762 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd43e0000")
8763 #elif defined(__POWERPC__)
8764 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("li r0, 20\nsc\nnop\nli r0, 37\nli r4, 2\nsc\nnop\n" \
8765 : : : "memory","r0","r3","r4" ) /* NOLINT */
8766 #endif
8767
8768#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_IPHONE)
8769
8770 // use inline assembler
8771 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
8772 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3")
8773 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
8774 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd4200000")
8775 #elif defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
8776 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xe7f001f0")
8777 #elif defined(__arm__) && defined(__thumb__)
8778 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xde01")
8779 #endif
8780
8781#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX)
8782 // If we can use inline assembler, do it because this allows us to break
8783 // directly at the location of the failing check instead of breaking inside
8784 // raise() called from it, i.e. one stack frame below.
8785 #if defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386) || defined(__x86_64))
8786 #define CATCH_TRAP() asm volatile ("int $3") /* NOLINT */
8787 #else // Fall back to the generic way.
8788 #include <signal.h>
8789
8790 #define CATCH_TRAP() raise(SIGTRAP)
8791 #endif
8792#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
8793 #define CATCH_TRAP() __debugbreak()
8794#elif defined(__MINGW32__)
8795 extern "C" __declspec(dllimport) void __stdcall DebugBreak();
8796 #define CATCH_TRAP() DebugBreak()
8797#endif
8798
8799#ifndef CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER
8800 #ifdef CATCH_TRAP
8801 #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{ if( Catch::isDebuggerActive() ) { CATCH_TRAP(); } }()
8802 #else
8803 #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{}()
8804 #endif
8805#endif

8933#include <cassert>
8934
8935namespace Catch {
8936
8947 class FatalConditionHandler {
8948 bool m_started = false;
8949
8950 // Install/disengage implementation for specific platform.
8951 // Should be if-defed to work on current platform, can assume
8952 // engage-disengage 1:1 pairing.
8953 void engage_platform();
8954 void disengage_platform() noexcept;
8955 public:
8956 // Should also have platform-specific implementations as needed
8957 FatalConditionHandler();
8958 ~FatalConditionHandler();
8959
8960 void engage() {
8961 assert(!m_started && "Handler cannot be installed twice.");
8962 m_started = true;
8963 engage_platform();
8964 }
8965
8966 void disengage() noexcept {
8967 assert(m_started && "Handler cannot be uninstalled without being installed first");
8968 m_started = false;
8969 disengage_platform();
8970 }
8971 };
8972
8974 class FatalConditionHandlerGuard {
8975 FatalConditionHandler* m_handler;
8976 public:
8977 FatalConditionHandlerGuard(FatalConditionHandler* handler):
8978 m_handler(handler) {
8979 m_handler->engage();
8980 }
8981 ~FatalConditionHandlerGuard() {
8982 m_handler->disengage();
8983 }
8984 };
8985
8986} // end namespace Catch

8991#ifndef CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
8992#define CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED

8994
8995
8996#ifndef CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
8997#define CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
8998
8999namespace Catch {
9000 bool isnan(float f);
9001 bool isnan(double d);
9002}
9003
9004#endif // CATCH_POLYFILLS_HPP_INCLUDED
9005
9006#include <cassert>
9007#include <cmath>
9008#include <cstdint>
9009#include <utility>
9010#include <limits>
9011
9012namespace Catch {
9013 namespace Detail {
9014
9015 uint32_t convertToBits(float f);
9016 uint64_t convertToBits(double d);
9017
9018 } // end namespace Detail
9019
9020
9021
9022#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
9023# pragma GCC diagnostic push
9024 // We do a bunch of direct compensations of floating point numbers,
9025 // because we know what we are doing and actually do want the direct
9026 // comparison behaviour.
9027# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
9028#endif
9029
9047 template <typename FP>
9048 uint64_t ulpDistance( FP lhs, FP rhs ) {
9049 assert( std::numeric_limits<FP>::is_iec559 &&
9050 "ulpDistance assumes IEEE-754 format for floating point types" );
9051 assert( !Catch::isnan( lhs ) &&
9052 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
9053 assert( !Catch::isnan( rhs ) &&
9054 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
9055
9056 // We want X == Y to imply 0 ULP distance even if X and Y aren't
9057 // bit-equal (-0 and 0), or X - Y != 0 (same sign infinities).
9058 if ( lhs == rhs ) { return 0; }
9059
9060 // We need a properly typed positive zero for type inference.
9061 static constexpr FP positive_zero{};
9062
9063 // We want to ensure that +/- 0 is always represented as positive zero
9064 if ( lhs == positive_zero ) { lhs = positive_zero; }
9065 if ( rhs == positive_zero ) { rhs = positive_zero; }
9066
9067 // If arguments have different signs, we can handle them by summing
9068 // how far are they from 0 each.
9069 if ( std::signbit( lhs ) != std::signbit( rhs ) ) {
9070 return ulpDistance( std::abs( lhs ), positive_zero ) +
9071 ulpDistance( std::abs( rhs ), positive_zero );
9072 }
9073
9074 // When both lhs and rhs are of the same sign, we can just
9075 // read the numbers bitwise as integers, and then subtract them
9076 // (assuming IEEE).
9077 uint64_t lc = Detail::convertToBits( lhs );
9078 uint64_t rc = Detail::convertToBits( rhs );
9079
9080 // The ulp distance between two numbers is symmetric, so to avoid
9081 // dealing with overflows we want the bigger converted number on the lhs
9082 if ( lc < rc ) {
9083 std::swap( lc, rc );
9084 }
9085
9086 return lc - rc;
9087 }
9088
9089#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
9090# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
9091#endif
9092
9093
9094} // end namespace Catch
9095
9096#endif // CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
9097

9100#define CATCH_GETENV_HPP_INCLUDED

9114#ifndef CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
9115#define CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
9116
9117#include <algorithm>
9118#include <iterator>
9119
9120namespace Catch {
9121 namespace Detail {
9122
9123 template <typename ForwardIter,
9124 typename Sentinel,
9125 typename T,
9126 typename Comparator>
9127 ForwardIter find_sentinel( ForwardIter start,
9128 Sentinel sentinel,
9129 T const& value,
9130 Comparator cmp ) {
9131 while ( start != sentinel ) {
9132 if ( cmp( *start, value ) ) { break; }
9133 ++start;
9134 }
9135 return start;
9136 }
9137
9138 template <typename ForwardIter,
9139 typename Sentinel,
9140 typename T,
9141 typename Comparator>
9142 std::ptrdiff_t count_sentinel( ForwardIter start,
9143 Sentinel sentinel,
9144 T const& value,
9145 Comparator cmp ) {
9146 std::ptrdiff_t count = 0;
9147 while ( start != sentinel ) {
9148 if ( cmp( *start, value ) ) { ++count; }
9149 ++start;
9150 }
9151 return count;
9152 }
9153
9154 template <typename ForwardIter, typename Sentinel>
9155 std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<ForwardIter, Sentinel>::value,
9156 std::ptrdiff_t>
9157 sentinel_distance( ForwardIter iter, const Sentinel sentinel ) {
9158 std::ptrdiff_t dist = 0;
9159 while ( iter != sentinel ) {
9160 ++iter;
9161 ++dist;
9162 }
9163 return dist;
9164 }
9165
9166 template <typename ForwardIter>
9167 std::ptrdiff_t sentinel_distance( ForwardIter first,
9168 ForwardIter last ) {
9169 return std::distance( first, last );
9170 }
9171
9172 template <typename ForwardIter1,
9173 typename Sentinel1,
9174 typename ForwardIter2,
9175 typename Sentinel2,
9176 typename Comparator>
9177 bool check_element_counts( ForwardIter1 first_1,
9178 const Sentinel1 end_1,
9179 ForwardIter2 first_2,
9180 const Sentinel2 end_2,
9181 Comparator cmp ) {
9182 auto cursor = first_1;
9183 while ( cursor != end_1 ) {
9184 if ( find_sentinel( first_1, cursor, *cursor, cmp ) ==
9185 cursor ) {
9186 // we haven't checked this element yet
9187 const auto count_in_range_2 =
9188 count_sentinel( first_2, end_2, *cursor, cmp );
9189 // Not a single instance in 2nd range, so it cannot be a
9190 // permutation of 1st range
9191 if ( count_in_range_2 == 0 ) { return false; }
9192
9193 const auto count_in_range_1 =
9194 count_sentinel( cursor, end_1, *cursor, cmp );
9195 if ( count_in_range_1 != count_in_range_2 ) {
9196 return false;
9197 }
9198 }
9199
9200 ++cursor;
9201 }
9202
9203 return true;
9204 }
9205
9206 template <typename ForwardIter1,
9207 typename Sentinel1,
9208 typename ForwardIter2,
9209 typename Sentinel2,
9210 typename Comparator>
9211 bool is_permutation( ForwardIter1 first_1,
9212 const Sentinel1 end_1,
9213 ForwardIter2 first_2,
9214 const Sentinel2 end_2,
9215 Comparator cmp ) {
9216 // TODO: no optimization for stronger iterators, because we would also have to constrain on sentinel vs not sentinel types
9217 // TODO: Comparator has to be "both sides", e.g. a == b => b == a
9218 // This skips shared prefix of the two ranges
9219 while (first_1 != end_1 && first_2 != end_2 && cmp(*first_1, *first_2)) {
9220 ++first_1;
9221 ++first_2;
9222 }
9223
9224 // We need to handle case where at least one of the ranges has no more elements
9225 if (first_1 == end_1 || first_2 == end_2) {
9226 return first_1 == end_1 && first_2 == end_2;
9227 }
9228
9229 // pair counting is n**2, so we pay linear walk to compare the sizes first
9230 auto dist_1 = sentinel_distance( first_1, end_1 );
9231 auto dist_2 = sentinel_distance( first_2, end_2 );
9232
9233 if (dist_1 != dist_2) { return false; }
9234
9235 // Since we do not try to handle stronger iterators pair (e.g.
9236 // bidir) optimally, the only thing left to do is to check counts in
9237 // the remaining ranges.
9238 return check_element_counts( first_1, end_1, first_2, end_2, cmp );
9239 }
9240
9241 } // namespace Detail
9242} // namespace Catch
9243
9244#endif // CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
9245

9538 struct NameAndLocation {
9539 std::string name;
9540 SourceLineInfo location;
9541
9542 NameAndLocation( std::string&& _name, SourceLineInfo const& _location );
9543 friend bool operator==(NameAndLocation const& lhs, NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
9544 // This is a very cheap check that should have a very high hit rate.
9545 // If we get to SourceLineInfo::operator==, we will redo it, but the
9546 // cost of repeating is trivial at that point (we will be paying
9547 // multiple strcmp/memcmps at that point).
9548 if ( lhs.location.line != rhs.location.line ) { return false; }
9549 return lhs.name == rhs.name && lhs.location == rhs.location;
9550 }
9551 friend bool operator!=(NameAndLocation const& lhs,
9552 NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
9553 return !( lhs == rhs );
9554 }
9555 };
9556
9564 struct NameAndLocationRef {
9565 StringRef name;
9566 SourceLineInfo location;
9567
9568 constexpr NameAndLocationRef( StringRef name_,
9569 SourceLineInfo location_ ):
9570 name( name_ ), location( location_ ) {}
9571
9572 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocation const& lhs,
9573 NameAndLocationRef const& rhs ) {
9574 // This is a very cheap check that should have a very high hit rate.
9575 // If we get to SourceLineInfo::operator==, we will redo it, but the
9576 // cost of repeating is trivial at that point (we will be paying
9577 // multiple strcmp/memcmps at that point).
9578 if ( lhs.location.line != rhs.location.line ) { return false; }
9579 return StringRef( lhs.name ) == rhs.name &&
9580 lhs.location == rhs.location;
9581 }
9582 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocationRef const& lhs,
9583 NameAndLocation const& rhs ) {
9584 return rhs == lhs;
9585 }
9586 };
9587
9588 class ITracker;

9592 class ITracker {
9593 NameAndLocation m_nameAndLocation;
9594
9595 using Children = std::vector<ITrackerPtr>;
9596
9597 protected:
9598 enum CycleState {
9599 NotStarted,
9600 Executing,
9601 ExecutingChildren,
9602 NeedsAnotherRun,
9603 CompletedSuccessfully,
9604 Failed
9605 };
9606
9607 ITracker* m_parent = nullptr;
9608 Children m_children;
9609 CycleState m_runState = NotStarted;
9610
9611 public:
9612 ITracker( NameAndLocation&& nameAndLoc, ITracker* parent ):
9613 m_nameAndLocation( CATCH_MOVE(nameAndLoc) ),
9614 m_parent( parent )
9615 {}
9616
9617
9618 // static queries
9619 NameAndLocation const& nameAndLocation() const {
9620 return m_nameAndLocation;
9621 }

9623 return m_parent;
9624 }

9627
9628
9629 // dynamic queries

9634 bool isSuccessfullyCompleted() const {
9635 return m_runState == CompletedSuccessfully;
9636 }
9637
9638 bool isOpen() const;
9640 bool hasStarted() const;
9641
9642 // actions
9643 virtual void close() = 0; // Successfully complete
9644 virtual void fail() = 0;
9645 void markAsNeedingAnotherRun();
9646
9648 void addChild( ITrackerPtr&& child );
9654 ITracker* findChild( NameAndLocationRef const& nameAndLocation );
9656 bool hasChildren() const {
9657 return !m_children.empty();
9658 }
9659
9660
9662 void openChild();
9663
9670 virtual bool isSectionTracker() const;
9677 virtual bool isGeneratorTracker() const;
9678 };

9903#ifndef CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
9904#define CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
9905
9906
9907#include <cmath>
9908#include <algorithm>
9909
9910namespace Catch {
9911
9912 template<typename Container>
9913 Container createShard(Container const& container, std::size_t const shardCount, std::size_t const shardIndex) {
9914 assert(shardCount > shardIndex);
9915
9916 if (shardCount == 1) {
9917 return container;
9918 }
9919
9920 const std::size_t totalTestCount = container.size();
9921
9922 const std::size_t shardSize = totalTestCount / shardCount;
9923 const std::size_t leftoverTests = totalTestCount % shardCount;
9924
9925 const std::size_t startIndex = shardIndex * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex, leftoverTests);
9926 const std::size_t endIndex = (shardIndex + 1) * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex + 1, leftoverTests);
9927
9928 auto startIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(startIndex));
9929 auto endIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(endIndex));
9930
9931 return Container(startIterator, endIterator);
9932 }
9933
9934}
9935
9936#endif // CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED

9939#ifndef CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED
9940#define CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED
9941
9942namespace Catch {
9943
9944 struct ISingleton {
9945 virtual ~ISingleton(); // = default
9946 };
9947
9948
9949 void addSingleton( ISingleton* singleton );
9950 void cleanupSingletons();
9951
9952
9953 template<typename SingletonImplT, typename InterfaceT = SingletonImplT, typename MutableInterfaceT = InterfaceT>
9954 class Singleton : SingletonImplT, public ISingleton {
9955
9956 static auto getInternal() -> Singleton* {
9957 static Singleton* s_instance = nullptr;
9958 if( !s_instance ) {
9959 s_instance = new Singleton;
9960 addSingleton( s_instance );
9961 }
9962 return s_instance;
9963 }
9964
9965 public:
9966 static auto get() -> InterfaceT const& {
9967 return *getInternal();
9968 }
9969 static auto getMutable() -> MutableInterfaceT& {
9970 return *getInternal();
9971 }
9972 };
9973
9974} // namespace Catch
9975
9976#endif // CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED

10260
10261 class Columns;
10262
10270 class Column {
10271 // String to be written out
10272 std::string m_string;
10273 // Width of the column for linebreaking
10274 size_t m_width = CATCH_CONFIG_CONSOLE_WIDTH - 1;
10275 // Indentation of other lines (including first if initial indent is unset)
10276 size_t m_indent = 0;
10277 // Indentation of the first line
10278 size_t m_initialIndent = std::string::npos;
10279
10280 public:
10284 class const_iterator {
10285 friend Column;
10286 struct EndTag {};
10287
10288 Column const& m_column;
10289 // Where does the current line start?
10290 size_t m_lineStart = 0;
10291 // How long should the current line be?
10292 size_t m_lineLength = 0;
10293 // How far have we checked the string to iterate?
10294 size_t m_parsedTo = 0;
10295 // Should a '-' be appended to the line?
10296 bool m_addHyphen = false;
10297
10298 const_iterator( Column const& column, EndTag ):
10299 m_column( column ), m_lineStart( m_column.m_string.size() ) {}
10300
10301 // Calculates the length of the current line
10302 void calcLength();
10303
10304 // Returns current indentation width
10305 size_t indentSize() const;
10306
10307 // Creates an indented and (optionally) suffixed string from
10308 // current iterator position, indentation and length.
10309 std::string addIndentAndSuffix( size_t position,
10310 size_t length ) const;
10311
10312 public:
10313 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
10314 using value_type = std::string;
10315 using pointer = value_type*;
10316 using reference = value_type&;
10317 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
10318
10319 explicit const_iterator( Column const& column );
10320
10321 std::string operator*() const;
10322
10323 const_iterator& operator++();
10324 const_iterator operator++( int );
10325
10326 bool operator==( const_iterator const& other ) const {
10327 return m_lineStart == other.m_lineStart && &m_column == &other.m_column;
10328 }
10329 bool operator!=( const_iterator const& other ) const {
10330 return !operator==( other );
10331 }
10332 };
10333 using iterator = const_iterator;
10334
10335 explicit Column( std::string const& text ): m_string( text ) {}
10336
10337 Column& width( size_t newWidth ) {
10338 assert( newWidth > 0 );
10339 m_width = newWidth;
10340 return *this;
10341 }
10342 Column& indent( size_t newIndent ) {
10343 m_indent = newIndent;
10344 return *this;
10345 }
10346 Column& initialIndent( size_t newIndent ) {
10347 m_initialIndent = newIndent;
10348 return *this;
10349 }
10350
10351 size_t width() const { return m_width; }
10352 const_iterator begin() const { return const_iterator( *this ); }
10353 const_iterator end() const { return { *this, const_iterator::EndTag{} }; }
10354
10355 friend std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream& os,
10356 Column const& col );
10357
10358 Columns operator+( Column const& other );
10359 };
10360
10362 Column Spacer( size_t spaceWidth );
10363
10364 class Columns {
10365 std::vector<Column> m_columns;
10366
10367 public:
10368 class iterator {
10369 friend Columns;
10370 struct EndTag {};
10371
10372 std::vector<Column> const& m_columns;
10373 std::vector<Column::const_iterator> m_iterators;
10374 size_t m_activeIterators;
10375
10376 iterator( Columns const& columns, EndTag );
10377
10378 public:
10379 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
10380 using value_type = std::string;
10381 using pointer = value_type*;
10382 using reference = value_type&;
10383 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
10384
10385 explicit iterator( Columns const& columns );
10386
10387 auto operator==( iterator const& other ) const -> bool {
10388 return m_iterators == other.m_iterators;
10389 }
10390 auto operator!=( iterator const& other ) const -> bool {
10391 return m_iterators != other.m_iterators;
10392 }
10393 std::string operator*() const;
10394 iterator& operator++();
10395 iterator operator++( int );
10396 };
10397 using const_iterator = iterator;
10398
10399 iterator begin() const { return iterator( *this ); }
10400 iterator end() const { return { *this, iterator::EndTag() }; }
10401
10402 Columns& operator+=( Column const& col );
10403 Columns operator+( Column const& col );
10404
10405 friend std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream& os,
10406 Columns const& cols );

10621 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
10622 class MatchExpr : public ITransientExpression {
10623 ArgT && m_arg;
10624 MatcherT const& m_matcher;
10625 public:
10626 MatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher )
10627 : ITransientExpression{ true, matcher.match( arg ) }, // not forwarding arg here on purpose
10628 m_arg( CATCH_FORWARD(arg) ),
10629 m_matcher( matcher )
10630 {}
10631
10632 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream& os ) const override {
10633 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_arg )
10634 << ' '
10635 << m_matcher.toString();
10636 }
10637 };

10641 class MatcherBase;
10642 }

10644 using StringMatcher = Matchers::MatcherBase<std::string>;
10645
10646 void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, StringMatcher const& matcher );
10647
10648 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
10649 auto makeMatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher ) -> MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT> {
10650 return MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT>( CATCH_FORWARD(arg), matcher );
10651 }

10657#define INTERNAL_CHECK_THAT( macroName, matcher, resultDisposition, arg ) \
10658 do { \
10659 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(arg) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
10660 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
10661 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( arg, matcher ) ); \
10662 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10663 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10664 } while( false )
10665
10666
10668#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_MATCHES( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
10669 do { \
10670 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
10671 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
10672 try { \
10673 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__ ); \
10674 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
10675 } \
10676 catch( exceptionType const& ex ) { \
10677 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( ex, matcher ) ); \
10678 } \
10679 catch( ... ) { \
10680 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
10681 } \
10682 else \
10683 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
10684 INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
10685 } while( false )
10686

10715 template<typename T>
10716 class MatcherBase : public MatcherUntypedBase {
10717 public:
10718 virtual bool match( T const& arg ) const = 0;
10719 };
