10721 namespace Detail {
10722
10723 template<typename ArgT>
10724 class MatchAllOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10725 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
10726
10727 public:
10728 MatchAllOf() = default;
10729 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
10730 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
10731 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
10732 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
10733
10734
10735 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10736 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10737 if (!matcher->match(arg))
10738 return false;
10739 }
10740 return true;
10741 }
10742 std::string describe() const override {
10743 std::string description;
10744 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
10745 description += "( ";
10746 bool first = true;
10747 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10748 if( first )
10749 first = false;
10750 else
10751 description += " and ";
10752 description += matcher->toString();
10753 }
10754 description += " )";
10755 return description;
10756 }
10757
10758 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatchAllOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
10759 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
10760 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
10761 }
10762 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf&& rhs) {
10763 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
10764 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
10765 }
10766 };
10767
10770 template<typename ArgT>
10771 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10774 template<typename ArgT>
10775 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10776
10777 template<typename ArgT>
10778 class MatchAnyOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10779 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
10780 public:
10781 MatchAnyOf() = default;
10782 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
10783 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
10784 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
10785 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
10786
10787 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10788 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10789 if (matcher->match(arg))
10790 return true;
10791 }
10792 return false;
10793 }
10794 std::string describe() const override {
10795 std::string description;
10796 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
10797 description += "( ";
10798 bool first = true;
10799 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
10800 if( first )
10801 first = false;
10802 else
10803 description += " or ";
10804 description += matcher->toString();
10805 }
10806 description += " )";
10807 return description;
10808 }
10809
10810 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatchAnyOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
10811 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
10812 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
10813 }
10814 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf&& rhs) {
10815 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
10816 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
10817 }
10818 };
10819
10822 template<typename ArgT>
10823 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10826 template<typename ArgT>
10827 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
10828
10829 template<typename ArgT>
10830 class MatchNotOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
10831 MatcherBase<ArgT> const& m_underlyingMatcher;
10832
10833 public:
10834 explicit MatchNotOf( MatcherBase<ArgT> const& underlyingMatcher ):
10835 m_underlyingMatcher( underlyingMatcher )
10836 {}
10837
10838 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
10839 return !m_underlyingMatcher.match( arg );
10840 }
10841
10842 std::string describe() const override {
10843 return "not " + m_underlyingMatcher.toString();
10844 }
10845 };
10846
10847 } // namespace Detail
10848
10849 template <typename T>
10850 Detail::MatchAllOf<T> operator&& (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
10851 return Detail::MatchAllOf<T>{} && lhs && rhs;
10852 }
10853 template <typename T>
10854 Detail::MatchAnyOf<T> operator|| (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
10855 return Detail::MatchAnyOf<T>{} || lhs || rhs;
10856 }
10857
10858 template <typename T>
10859 Detail::MatchNotOf<T> operator! (MatcherBase<T> const& matcher) {
10860 return Detail::MatchNotOf<T>{ matcher };
10861 }

10946 template<std::size_t N, std::size_t M>
10947 std::array<void const*, N + M> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, std::array<void const*, M> && rhs) {
10948 std::array<void const*, N + M> arr{};
10949 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
10950 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), M, arr.begin() + N);
10951 return arr;
10952 }
10953
10954 template<std::size_t N>
10955 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, void const* rhs) {
10956 std::array<void const*, N+1> arr{};
10957 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
10958 arr[N] = rhs;
10959 return arr;
10960 }
10961
10962 template<std::size_t N>
10963 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(void const* lhs, std::array<void const*, N> && rhs) {
10964 std::array<void const*, N + 1> arr{ {lhs} };
10965 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), N, arr.begin() + 1);
10966 return arr;
10967 }
10968
10969 template<typename T>
10970 using is_generic_matcher = std::is_base_of<
10971 Catch::Matchers::MatcherGenericBase,
10972 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
10973 >;
10974
10975 template<typename... Ts>
10976 using are_generic_matchers = Catch::Detail::conjunction<is_generic_matcher<Ts>...>;
10977
10978 template<typename T>
10979 using is_matcher = std::is_base_of<
10980 Catch::Matchers::MatcherUntypedBase,
10981 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
10982 >;
10983
10984
10985 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
10986 bool match_all_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
10987 return true;
10988 }
10989
10990 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
10991 bool match_all_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
10992 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) && match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
10993 }
10994
10995
10996 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
10997 bool match_any_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
10998 return false;
10999 }
11000
11001 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
11002 bool match_any_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
11003 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) || match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
11004 }
11005
11006 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::string const* descriptions_begin, std::string const* descriptions_end);
11007
11008 template<typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t... Idx>
11009 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx...>) {
11010 std::array<std::string, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> descriptions {{
11011 static_cast<MatcherTs const*>(matchers[Idx])->toString()...
11012 }};
11013
11014 return describe_multi_matcher(combine, descriptions.data(), descriptions.data() + descriptions.size());
11015 }
11016
11017
11018 template<typename... MatcherTs>
11019 class MatchAllOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11020 public:
11021 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11022 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11023 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
11024 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
11025
11026 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
11027 explicit MatchAllOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
11028
11029 template<typename Arg>
11030 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
11031 return match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
11032 }
11033
11034 std::string describe() const override {
11035 return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" and "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
11036 }
11037
11038 // Has to be public to enable the concatenating operators
11039 // below, because they are not friend of the RHS, only LHS,
11040 // and thus cannot access private fields of RHS
11041 std::array<void const*, sizeof...( MatcherTs )> m_matchers;
11042
11043
11045 template<typename... MatchersRHS>
11046 friend
11047 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator && (
11048 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
11049 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
11050 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
11051 }
11052
11054 template<typename MatcherRHS>
11055 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value,
11056 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator && (
11057 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
11058 MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11059 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(&rhs))};
11060 }
11061
11063 template<typename MatcherLHS>
11064 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value,
11065 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator && (
11066 MatcherLHS const& lhs,
11067 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
11068 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
11069 }
11070 };
11071
11072
11073 template<typename... MatcherTs>
11074 class MatchAnyOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11075 public:
11076 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11077 MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11078 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
11079 MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
11080
11081 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
11082 explicit MatchAnyOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
11083
11084 template<typename Arg>
11085 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
11086 return match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
11087 }
11088
11089 std::string describe() const override {
11090 return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" or "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
11091 }
11092
11093
11094 // Has to be public to enable the concatenating operators
11095 // below, because they are not friend of the RHS, only LHS,
11096 // and thus cannot access private fields of RHS
11097 std::array<void const*, sizeof...( MatcherTs )> m_matchers;
11098
11100 template<typename... MatchersRHS>
11101 friend MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator || (
11102 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
11103 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
11104 return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
11105 }
11106
11108 template<typename MatcherRHS>
11109 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value,
11110 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator || (
11111 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
11112 MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11113 return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(rhs)))};
11114 }
11115
11117 template<typename MatcherLHS>
11118 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value,
11119 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator || (
11120 MatcherLHS const& lhs,
11121 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
11122 return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
11123 }
11124 };
11125
11126
11127 template<typename MatcherT>
11128 class MatchNotOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11129 MatcherT const& m_matcher;
11130
11131 public:
11132 MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11133 MatchNotOfGeneric& operator=(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
11134 MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric&&) = default;
11135 MatchNotOfGeneric& operator=(MatchNotOfGeneric&&) = default;
11136
11137 explicit MatchNotOfGeneric(MatcherT const& matcher) : m_matcher{matcher} {}
11138
11139 template<typename Arg>
11140 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
11141 return !m_matcher.match(arg);
11142 }
11143
11144 std::string describe() const override {
11145 return "not " + m_matcher.toString();
11146 }
11147
11149 friend MatcherT const& operator ! (MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT> const& matcher) {
11150 return matcher.m_matcher;
11151 }
11152 };
11153 } // namespace Detail

11156 // compose only generic matchers
11157 template<typename MatcherLHS, typename MatcherRHS>
11158 std::enable_if_t<Detail::are_generic_matchers<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>::value, Detail::MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>>
11159 operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11160 return { lhs, rhs };
11161 }
11162
11163 template<typename MatcherLHS, typename MatcherRHS>
11164 std::enable_if_t<Detail::are_generic_matchers<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>::value, Detail::MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>>
11165 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11166 return { lhs, rhs };
11167 }
11168
11170 template<typename MatcherT>
11171 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherT>::value, Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>>
11172 operator ! (MatcherT const& matcher) {
11173 return Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>{matcher};
11174 }
11175
11176
11177 // compose mixed generic and non-generic matchers
11178 template<typename MatcherLHS, typename ArgRHS>
11179 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value, Detail::MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherBase<ArgRHS>>>
11180 operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {
11181 return { lhs, rhs };
11182 }
11183
11184 template<typename ArgLHS, typename MatcherRHS>
11185 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value, Detail::MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherBase<ArgLHS>, MatcherRHS>>
11186 operator && (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11187 return { lhs, rhs };
11188 }
11189
11190 template<typename MatcherLHS, typename ArgRHS>
11191 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value, Detail::MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherBase<ArgRHS>>>
11192 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {
11193 return { lhs, rhs };
11194 }
11195
11196 template<typename ArgLHS, typename MatcherRHS>
11197 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_generic_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value, Detail::MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherBase<ArgLHS>, MatcherRHS>>
11198 operator || (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
11199 return { lhs, rhs };
11200 }

11225 class HasSizeMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {

11227 public:
11228 explicit HasSizeMatcher(std::size_t target_size):
11229 m_target_size(target_size)
11230 {}
11231
11232 template <typename RangeLike>
11233 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11234#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
11235 using Catch::Detail::size;

11237 using std::size;
11238#endif
11239 return size(rng) == m_target_size;
11240 }

11245 template <typename Matcher>
11246 class SizeMatchesMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11247 Matcher m_matcher;
11248 public:
11249 explicit SizeMatchesMatcher(Matcher m):
11250 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(m))
11251 {}
11252
11253 template <typename RangeLike>
11254 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11255#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
11256 using Catch::Detail::size;
11257#else
11258 using std::size;
11259#endif
11260 return m_matcher.match(size(rng));
11261 }

11264 return "size matches " + m_matcher.describe();

11295 template <typename T, typename Equality>
11296 class ContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11297 T m_desired;
11298 Equality m_eq;
11299 public:
11300 template <typename T2, typename Equality2>
11301 ContainsElementMatcher(T2&& target, Equality2&& predicate):
11302 m_desired(CATCH_FORWARD(target)),
11303 m_eq(CATCH_FORWARD(predicate))
11304 {}
11305
11306 std::string describe() const override {
11307 return "contains element " + Catch::Detail::stringify(m_desired);
11308 }
11309
11310 template <typename RangeLike>
11311 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
11312 for ( auto&& elem : rng ) {
11313 if ( m_eq( elem, m_desired ) ) { return true; }
11314 }
11315 return false;
11316 }
11317 };
11318
11320 template <typename Matcher>
11321 class ContainsMatcherMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11322 Matcher m_matcher;
11323 public:
11324 // Note that we do a copy+move to avoid having to SFINAE this
11325 // constructor (and also avoid some perfect forwarding failure
11326 // cases)
11327 ContainsMatcherMatcher(Matcher matcher):
11328 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(matcher))
11329 {}
11330
11331 template <typename RangeLike>
11332 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11333 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
11334 if (m_matcher.match(elem)) {
11335 return true;
11336 }
11337 }
11338 return false;
11339 }
11340
11341 std::string describe() const override {
11342 return "contains element matching " + m_matcher.describe();
11343 }
11344 };
11345
11351 template <typename T>
11352 std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_matcher<T>::value,
11353 ContainsElementMatcher<T, std::equal_to<>>> Contains(T&& elem) {
11354 return { CATCH_FORWARD(elem), std::equal_to<>{} };
11355 }
11356
11358 template <typename Matcher>
11359 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher<Matcher>::value,
11360 ContainsMatcherMatcher<Matcher>> Contains(Matcher&& matcher) {
11361 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
11362 }
11363
11369 template <typename T, typename Equality>
11370 ContainsElementMatcher<T, Equality> Contains(T&& elem, Equality&& eq) {
11371 return { CATCH_FORWARD(elem), CATCH_FORWARD(eq) };
11372 }
11373
11374 }

11480
11481 // Given IEEE-754 format for floats and doubles, we can assume
11482 // that float -> double promotion is lossless. Given this, we can
11483 // assume that if we do the standard relative comparison of
11484 // |lhs - rhs| <= epsilon * max(fabs(lhs), fabs(rhs)), then we get
11485 // the same result if we do this for floats, as if we do this for
11486 // doubles that were promoted from floats.
11487 class WithinRelMatcher final : public MatcherBase<double> {
11488 public:
11489 WithinRelMatcher( double target, double epsilon );
11490 bool match(double const& matchee) const override;
11491 std::string describe() const override;
11492 private:
11493 double m_target;
11494 double m_epsilon;
11495 };
11496
11498 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target, double eps);
11500 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target);
11502 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target, float eps);
11504 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target);
11505

11510 IsNaNMatcher() = default;
11511 bool match( double const& matchee ) const override;
11512 std::string describe() const override;
11513 };

11536template <typename T, typename Predicate>
11537class PredicateMatcher final : public MatcherBase<T> {
11538 Predicate m_predicate;
11539 std::string m_description;
11540public:
11541
11542 PredicateMatcher(Predicate&& elem, std::string const& descr)
11543 :m_predicate(CATCH_FORWARD(elem)),
11544 m_description(Detail::finalizeDescription(descr))
11545 {}
11546
11547 bool match( T const& item ) const override {
11548 return m_predicate(item);
11549 }
11550
11551 std::string describe() const override {
11552 return m_description;
11553 }
11554};
11555
11561 template<typename T, typename Pred>
11562 PredicateMatcher<T, Pred> Predicate(Pred&& predicate, std::string const& description = "") {
11563 static_assert(is_callable<Pred(T)>::value, "Predicate not callable with argument T");
11564 static_assert(std::is_same<bool, FunctionReturnType<Pred, T>>::value, "Predicate does not return bool");
11565 return PredicateMatcher<T, Pred>(CATCH_FORWARD(predicate), description);
11566 }

11580 // Matcher for checking that all elements in range matches a given matcher.
11581 template <typename Matcher>
11582 class AllMatchMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11583 Matcher m_matcher;
11584 public:
11585 AllMatchMatcher(Matcher matcher):
11586 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(matcher))
11587 {}
11588
11589 std::string describe() const override {
11590 return "all match " + m_matcher.describe();
11591 }
11592
11593 template <typename RangeLike>
11594 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11595 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
11596 if (!m_matcher.match(elem)) {
11597 return false;
11598 }
11599 }
11600 return true;
11601 }
11602 };

11614 return "none match " + m_matcher.describe();

11620 if (m_matcher.match(elem)) {
11621 return false;
11622 }
11623 }
11624 return true;
11625 }

11645 return true;

11652 // Matcher for checking that all elements in range are true.

11661 return false;

11668 // Matcher for checking that no element in range is true.
11669 class NoneTrueMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11670 public:
11671 std::string describe() const override;
11672
11673 template <typename RangeLike>
11674 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11675 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
11676 if (elem) {
11677 return false;
11678 }
11679 }
11680 return true;
11681 }
11682 };
11683
11684 // Matcher for checking that any element in range is true.
11685 class AnyTrueMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11686 public:
11687 std::string describe() const override;
11688
11689 template <typename RangeLike>
11690 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
11691 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
11692 if (elem) {
11693 return true;
11694 }
11695 }
11696 return false;
11697 }
11698 };
11699
11700 // Creates a matcher that checks whether all elements in a range match a matcher
11701 template <typename Matcher>
11702 AllMatchMatcher<Matcher> AllMatch(Matcher&& matcher) {
11703 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
11704 }
11705
11706 // Creates a matcher that checks whether no element in a range matches a matcher.
11707 template <typename Matcher>
11708 NoneMatchMatcher<Matcher> NoneMatch(Matcher&& matcher) {
11709 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
11710 }
11711
11712 // Creates a matcher that checks whether any element in a range matches a matcher.
11713 template <typename Matcher>
11714 AnyMatchMatcher<Matcher> AnyMatch(Matcher&& matcher) {
11715 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
11716 }
11717
11718 // Creates a matcher that checks whether all elements in a range are true
11719 AllTrueMatcher AllTrue();
11720
11721 // Creates a matcher that checks whether no element in a range is true
11722 NoneTrueMatcher NoneTrue();
11723
11724 // Creates a matcher that checks whether any element in a range is true
11725 AnyTrueMatcher AnyTrue();
11726 }
11727}

11729#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_QUANTIFIERS_HPP_INCLUDED

11732#ifndef CATCH_MATCHERS_RANGE_EQUALS_HPP_INCLUDED
11733#define CATCH_MATCHERS_RANGE_EQUALS_HPP_INCLUDED
11734
11735
11736#include <algorithm>
11737#include <utility>
11738
11739namespace Catch {
11740 namespace Matchers {
11741
11746 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
11747 class RangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11748 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
11749 Equality m_predicate;
11750
11751 public:
11752 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
11753 RangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
11754 Equality2&& predicate ):
11755 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
11756 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
11757
11758 template <typename RangeLike>
11759 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
11760 auto rng_start = begin( rng );
11761 const auto rng_end = end( rng );
11762 auto target_start = begin( m_desired );
11763 const auto target_end = end( m_desired );
11764
11765 while (rng_start != rng_end && target_start != target_end) {
11766 if (!m_predicate(*rng_start, *target_start)) {
11767 return false;
11768 }
11769 ++rng_start;
11770 ++target_start;
11771 }
11772 return rng_start == rng_end && target_start == target_end;
11773 }
11774
11775 std::string describe() const override {
11776 return "elements are " + Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
11777 }
11778 };
11779
11784 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
11785 class UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
11786 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
11787 Equality m_predicate;
11788
11789 public:
11790 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
11791 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
11792 Equality2&& predicate ):
11793 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
11794 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
11795
11796 template <typename RangeLike>
11797 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
11798 using std::begin;
11799 using std::end;
11800 return Catch::Detail::is_permutation( begin( m_desired ),
11801 end( m_desired ),
11802 begin( rng ),
11803 end( rng ),
11804 m_predicate );
11805 }
11806
11807 std::string describe() const override {
11808 return "unordered elements are " +
11809 ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
11810 }
11811 };
11812
11819 template <typename RangeLike>
11820 std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_matcher<RangeLike>::value,
11821 RangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, std::equal_to<>>>
11822 RangeEquals( RangeLike&& range ) {
11823 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), std::equal_to<>{} };
11824 }
11825
11832 template <typename RangeLike, typename Equality>
11833 RangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, Equality>
11834 RangeEquals( RangeLike&& range, Equality&& predicate ) {
11835 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
11836 }
11837
11844 template <typename RangeLike>
11845 std::enable_if_t<
11846 !Detail::is_matcher<RangeLike>::value,
11847 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, std::equal_to<>>>
11848 UnorderedRangeEquals( RangeLike&& range ) {
11849 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), std::equal_to<>{} };
11850 }
11851
11858 template <typename RangeLike, typename Equality>
11859 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, Equality>
11860 UnorderedRangeEquals( RangeLike&& range, Equality&& predicate ) {
11861 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
11862 }
11863 } // namespace Matchers
11864} // namespace Catch

11955 template<typename T, typename Alloc>
11956 class VectorContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, Alloc>> {
11957 T const& m_comparator;
11958
11959 public:
11960 VectorContainsElementMatcher(T const& comparator):
11961 m_comparator(comparator)
11962 {}
11963
11964 bool match(std::vector<T, Alloc> const& v) const override {
11965 for (auto const& el : v) {
11966 if (el == m_comparator) {
11967 return true;
11968 }
11969 }
11970 return false;
11971 }
11972
11973 std::string describe() const override {
11974 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
11975 }
11976 };
11977
11978 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
11979 class ContainsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
11980 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
11981
11982 public:
11983 ContainsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
11984 m_comparator( comparator )
11985 {}
11986
11987 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
11988 // !TBD: see note in EqualsMatcher
11989 if (m_comparator.size() > v.size())
11990 return false;
11991 for (auto const& comparator : m_comparator) {
11992 auto present = false;
11993 for (const auto& el : v) {
11994 if (el == comparator) {
11995 present = true;
11996 break;
11997 }
11998 }
11999 if (!present) {
12000 return false;
12001 }
12002 }
12003 return true;
12004 }
12005 std::string describe() const override {
12006 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
12007 }
12008 };
12009
12010 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
12011 class EqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
12012 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
12013
12014 public:
12015 EqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
12016 m_comparator( comparator )
12017 {}
12018
12019 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
12020 // !TBD: This currently works if all elements can be compared using !=
12021 // - a more general approach would be via a compare template that defaults
12022 // to using !=. but could be specialised for, e.g. std::vector<T> etc
12023 // - then just call that directly
12024 if ( m_comparator.size() != v.size() ) { return false; }
12025 for ( std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i ) {
12026 if ( !( m_comparator[i] == v[i] ) ) { return false; }
12027 }
12028 return true;
12029 }
12030 std::string describe() const override {
12031 return "Equals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
12032 }
12033 };
12034
12035 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
12036 class ApproxMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
12037 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
12038 mutable Catch::Approx approx = Catch::Approx::custom();
12039
12040 public:
12041 ApproxMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
12042 m_comparator( comparator )
12043 {}
12044
12045 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
12046 if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
12047 return false;
12048 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
12049 if (m_comparator[i] != approx(v[i]))
12050 return false;
12051 return true;
12052 }
12053 std::string describe() const override {
12054 return "is approx: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
12055 }
12056 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
12057 ApproxMatcher& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
12058 approx.epsilon(static_cast<double>(newEpsilon));
12059 return *this;
12060 }
12061 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
12062 ApproxMatcher& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
12063 approx.margin(static_cast<double>(newMargin));
12064 return *this;
12065 }
12066 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
12067 ApproxMatcher& scale( T const& newScale ) {
12068 approx.scale(static_cast<double>(newScale));
12069 return *this;
12070 }
12071 };
12072
12073 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
12074 class UnorderedEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
12075 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_target;
12076
12077 public:
12078 UnorderedEqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target):
12079 m_target(target)
12080 {}
12081 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& vec) const override {
12082 if (m_target.size() != vec.size()) {
12083 return false;
12084 }
12085 return std::is_permutation(m_target.begin(), m_target.end(), vec.begin());
12086 }
12087
12088 std::string describe() const override {
12089 return "UnorderedEquals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify(m_target);
12090 }
12091 };
12092

12095 // This allows the types to be inferred
12096
12098 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
12099 ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Contains( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
12100 return ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
12101 }

12104 template<typename T, typename Alloc = std::allocator<T>>
12105 VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc> VectorContains( T const& comparator ) {
12106 return VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc>(comparator);
12107 }
12108
12110 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
12111 EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Equals( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
12112 return EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
12113 }
12114
12116 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
12117 ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Approx( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
12118 return ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
12119 }
12120
12122 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
12123 UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> UnorderedEquals(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target) {
12124 return UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(target);
12125 }

12466 class CumulativeReporterBase : public ReporterBase {
12467 public:
12468 template<typename T, typename ChildNodeT>
12469 struct Node {
12470 explicit Node( T const& _value ) : value( _value ) {}
12471
12472 using ChildNodes = std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<ChildNodeT>>;
12473 T value;
12474 ChildNodes children;
12475 };
12476 struct SectionNode {
12477 explicit SectionNode(SectionStats const& _stats) : stats(_stats) {}
12478
12479 bool operator == (SectionNode const& other) const {
12480 return stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo == other.stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo;
12481 }
12482
12483 bool hasAnyAssertions() const;
12484
12485 SectionStats stats;
12486 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode>> childSections;
12487 std::vector<Detail::AssertionOrBenchmarkResult> assertionsAndBenchmarks;
12488 std::string stdOut;
12489 std::string stdErr;
12490 };
12491
12492
12493 using TestCaseNode = Node<TestCaseStats, SectionNode>;
12494 using TestRunNode = Node<TestRunStats, TestCaseNode>;
12495
12496 // GCC5 compat: we cannot use inherited constructor, because it
12497 // doesn't implement backport of P0136
12498 CumulativeReporterBase(ReporterConfig&& _config):
12499 ReporterBase(CATCH_MOVE(_config))
12500 {}
12501 ~CumulativeReporterBase() override;
12502
12503 void benchmarkPreparing( StringRef ) override {}
12504 void benchmarkStarting( BenchmarkInfo const& ) override {}
12505 void benchmarkEnded( BenchmarkStats<> const& benchmarkStats ) override;
12506 void benchmarkFailed( StringRef ) override {}
12507
12508 void noMatchingTestCases( StringRef ) override {}
12509 void reportInvalidTestSpec( StringRef ) override {}
12510 void fatalErrorEncountered( StringRef /*error*/ ) override {}
12511
12512 void testRunStarting( TestRunInfo const& ) override {}
12513
12514 void testCaseStarting( TestCaseInfo const& ) override {}
12515 void testCasePartialStarting( TestCaseInfo const&, uint64_t ) override {}
12516 void sectionStarting( SectionInfo const& sectionInfo ) override;
12517
12518 void assertionStarting( AssertionInfo const& ) override {}
12519
12520 void assertionEnded( AssertionStats const& assertionStats ) override;
12521 void sectionEnded( SectionStats const& sectionStats ) override;
12522 void testCasePartialEnded( TestCaseStats const&, uint64_t ) override {}
12523 void testCaseEnded( TestCaseStats const& testCaseStats ) override;
12524 void testRunEnded( TestRunStats const& testRunStats ) override;
12526 virtual void testRunEndedCumulative() = 0;
12527
12528 void skipTest(TestCaseInfo const&) override {}
12529
12530 protected:
12532 bool m_shouldStoreSuccesfulAssertions = true;
12534 bool m_shouldStoreFailedAssertions = true;
12535
12536 // We need lazy construction here. We should probably refactor it
12537 // later, after the events are redone.
12539 Detail::unique_ptr<TestRunNode> m_testRun;
12540
12541 private:
12542 // Note: We rely on pointer identity being stable, which is why
12543 // we store pointers to the nodes rather than the values.
12544 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<TestCaseNode>> m_testCases;
12545 // Root section of the _current_ test case
12546 Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode> m_rootSection;
12547 // Deepest section of the _current_ test case
12548 SectionNode* m_deepestSection = nullptr;
12549 // Stack of _active_ sections in the _current_ test case
12550 std::vector<SectionNode*> m_sectionStack;
12551 };
12552
12553} // end namespace Catch

12555#endif // CATCH_REPORTER_CUMULATIVE_BASE_HPP_INCLUDED

12821namespace Catch {

12824
12825 template <typename T, typename = void>
12826 struct has_description : std::false_type {};
12827
12828 template <typename T>
12829 struct has_description<
12830 T,
12831 void_t<decltype( T::getDescription() )>>
12832 : std::true_type {};
12833
12836 void registerReporterImpl( std::string const& name,
12837 IReporterFactoryPtr reporterPtr );
12839 void registerListenerImpl( Detail::unique_ptr<EventListenerFactory> listenerFactory );
12840 } // namespace Detail
12841
12842 class IEventListener;
12843 using IEventListenerPtr = Detail::unique_ptr<IEventListener>;
12844
12845 template <typename T>
12846 class ReporterFactory : public IReporterFactory {
12847
12848 IEventListenerPtr create( ReporterConfig&& config ) const override {
12849 return Detail::make_unique<T>( CATCH_MOVE(config) );
12850 }
12851
12852 std::string getDescription() const override {
12853 return T::getDescription();
12854 }
12855 };
12856
12857
12858 template<typename T>
12859 class ReporterRegistrar {
12860 public:
12861 explicit ReporterRegistrar( std::string const& name ) {
12862 registerReporterImpl( name,
12863 Detail::make_unique<ReporterFactory<T>>() );
12864 }
12865 };
12866
12867 template<typename T>
12868 class ListenerRegistrar {
12869
12870 class TypedListenerFactory : public EventListenerFactory {
12871 StringRef m_listenerName;
12872
12873 std::string getDescriptionImpl( std::true_type ) const {
12874 return T::getDescription();
12875 }
12876
12877 std::string getDescriptionImpl( std::false_type ) const {
12878 return "(No description provided)";
12879 }
12880
12881 public:
12882 TypedListenerFactory( StringRef listenerName ):
12883 m_listenerName( listenerName ) {}
12884
12885 IEventListenerPtr create( IConfig const* config ) const override {
12886 return Detail::make_unique<T>( config );
12887 }
12888
12889 StringRef getName() const override {
12890 return m_listenerName;
12891 }
12892
12893 std::string getDescription() const override {
12894 return getDescriptionImpl( Detail::has_description<T>{} );
12895 }
12896 };
12897
12898 public:
12899 ListenerRegistrar(StringRef listenerName) {
12900 registerListenerImpl( Detail::make_unique<TypedListenerFactory>(listenerName) );
12901 }
12902 };
12903}

12906
12907# define CATCH_REGISTER_REPORTER( name, reporterType ) \

12909 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
12910 namespace { \
12911 Catch::ReporterRegistrar<reporterType> INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( \
12912 catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( name ); \
12913 } \
12914 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
12915
12916# define CATCH_REGISTER_LISTENER( listenerType ) \
12917 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
12918 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
12919 namespace { \
12920 Catch::ListenerRegistrar<listenerType> INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( \
12921 catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( #listenerType##_catch_sr ); \
12922 } \
12923 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
12924
12925#else // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE
